title: no bake cookies
directions: Heat molasses, sugar and butter, but do not boil.
Add 2 cups peanut butter, pinch of salt and melt.
Add 3 quarts cornflakes. Do not bake.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Reduce the heat to medium, add milk and diced cream cheese and diced Velveeta cheese, stir constantly until cheeses are melted.
Add broccoli, cauliflower or asparagus which has been put in blender.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar, milk, egg yolks, and flour.
Add salt and butter. Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue. Bake until top browns.

title: spicy tomato-onion sauce(for hot dogs)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook and stir until heated through and bubbly.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into ring (a ring mold works well).
Serve with strawberry preserves in the middle of the ring. Arrange assorted crackers around the ring.

title: corn pudding
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in half and half.
Add well beaten eggs, salt, sugar, Accent and melted butter and mix thoroughly.
Add corn and stir well.
Bake pudding in dish.
Sit dish in pan with 1 1/2 to 2 inches of water.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° or until firm.

title: mother sawyers' stack cake
directions: Make dough as you would for cookies, adding enough plain flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll out thin and cut with desired size lid for uniform shape.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Cool slightly before adding apples.

title: apple goodies
directions: Place apples in a baking dish.
Cover with the sugar.
Mix butter, oats, flour and brown sugar together and spread over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Cook cake as directed.
Poke holes while warm and pour coffee over cake.
Crumble cake.
Layer as follows in trifle bowl: 1 layer cake, 1 layer mousse, 1 layer Cool Whip, 1 candy.
Repeat, ending with Cool Whip on top.

title: napa cabbage salad
directions: Combine cabbage and onions.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Combine flavor packet from soup mix, sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, break up noodles from soup mix into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well in blender.
Baste chicken with sauce on grill.

title: tiramisu
directions: Pour coffee in mixing bowl; add 1/3 cup rum. Set aside. In another bowl, beat eggs, then add mascarpone cheese, 1/4 cup of powdered sugar and rest of rum. Beat together until stiff. In another bowl, add 2 cups heavy cream, the rest of powdered sugar and dash of vanilla. Beat until stiff. Put together. Dip ladyfingers, one at a time, in coffee mix. Cover bottom of 9 x 13 dish. Layer cheese mix, then heavy cream. Mix and repeat. Dust with cocoa powder. Enjoy!

title: wacky cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except margarine and Ritz crackers; pour into baking dish. Melt margarine and mix with crushed Ritz crackers. Spread on top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rum balls
directions: Roll mixture in small balls.
Dip in powdered sugar.
Cookies may be frozen.

title: barbecue-style meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce. Form into loaf and put in shallow pan, about 7 x 10-inches. Combine the rest of the sauce and all other ingredients.
Pour over loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Baste occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: divinity
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water.
Boil until it forms a hard ball. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add syrup mixture to egg whites, beating constantly.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper or pour into buttered pan.

title: super spanish rice
directions: Melt the butter or margarine in a large skillet. Saute the ground beef until lightly browned and the vegetables are soft. Stir in the rice, tomatoes and sugar. When the mixture simmers, stir in the cheese, reserving a little to garnish the top. Pour into a large casserole and
bake uncovered
for one hour using long grain or brown rice, or 1/2 hour when using minute rice. Garnish with black and/or green stuffed olives and bell pepper strips if desired.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops, onion and pepper in oil.
Sprinkle with rice.
Add soup and half of water.
Boil for 30 to 35 minutes. Add remaining water as needed.

title: chicken turnovers
directions: Mix well.
Roll out refrigerated biscuits into flat circles. Place filling inside and fold over.
Seal.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes to a golden brown.

title: almond lemonade
directions: Mix lemonade with 4 cans water, vanilla and almond extract. In saucepan heat remaining 4 cans water with sugar and heat until water is clear.
Add to mixture and refrigerate.
Add 7-Up or ginger ale just before serving.

title: brick cake(sugar-free)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add the liquid, leaving milk for last to give the right texture.
Add raisins.
Pour into glass baking dishes.
Pour 1/2 to 3/4-inches deep (any deeper and it won't cook inside).
There should be enough to fill 2 glass dishes, depending on size.
I use one 9 x 13-inch and one 9 x 9-inch. Preheat oven to 350° and bake until done, 30 to 40 minutes.
(Cut into center and look to see if done.)
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt margarine and 1/2 cup sugar in a 9 x 12-inch glass pan. Cook until bubbly.
Pat pretzels into mixture.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix well the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix cornstarch into pineapple in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Cool and spread on mixture.

title: little pizza snacks
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Add ketchup and cheese to sausage and mix well, until cheese melts.
Put 1 1/2 teaspoons of mixture on each slice of bread.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes on cookie sheets.

title: furniture polish
directions: Use lemon juice or orange juice to paint a picture or message you can't see.
To reveal the message, either press with an iron or hold paper over a light bulb.

title: orange sherbet party punch
directions: Heat 2 cups water to boiling; add to gelatin and sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Add 2 cups cold water and fruit juices. Chill until ready to serve.
Just before serving, spoon in sherbet and pour in ginger ale.
Yield:
6 1/2 quarts.

title: any season salad
directions: Break cauliflower into small florets
Stem pieces can be cut into same size pieces.
Core apple and cut into pieces about same size as florets.
Do not peel.
Peel yam and shred on slaw cutter. Toss all ingredients with desired amount of vinaigrette.
Salad still good next day.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix together bread and corn bread that have been crumbled with the stock from turkey.
Be sure to use enough stock so it will not be stiff.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients.
Bake slowly for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: mud balls(fun and healthy snacks)
directions: Help your child mix the ingredients together and form into balls.

title: pea salad
directions: Cook peas according to directions and drain.
Dice everything together and mix well with dressing.

title: nutty cheese ring(a quick and delicious appetizer.)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well and shape into a ring.
Place on a platter.
Chill for several minutes or chill overnight for all flavors to blend.
Fill center of ring with preserves and serve with assorted crackers.
Makes 16 servings.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add eggs.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool.
Pipe whipped cream around edges.

title: pepparkakor
directions: Stir together all dry ingredients except orange.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat until fluffy. Stir in molasses and orange peel and juice.
Mix well.
Stir in flour; mix until blended.
Cover and chill until firm enough to roll out, several hours or overnight.
Remove small portions of dough at a time from refrigerator and roll out on lightly floured surface 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with fancy 2 1/2-inch cookie cutter.
Re-roll scraps.
Place 1-inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on rack. Decorate with royal icing.
Repeat with remainder of dough.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In a pan, mix 1 to 1 1/2 cups flour, salt and pepper.
Cut meat into small 1-inch thick strips and roll in flour.
In a deep frying pan, melt 1 stick oleo.
Shake excess flour from meat and brown it in the butter.
After meat has browned, add consomme and 1 can water.
Simmer until mixture begins to thicken.
Stir often.
(Some water can be added if it thickens too much, or begins to stick.) In another pan, melt 1/2 stick oleo.
Saute mushrooms and chopped onion until onion is transparent.
Add to meat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes more.
Stir well.
Just before serving, add 1 cup sour cream; serve over rice or noodles.
It's easy and tastes great.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: For 6 servings:
Dice and brown lean pork in bacon fat.
Cook until clear and thick.
Add pork and cook 1 hour covered.
A few minutes before serving, add thinly sliced green peppers and onion, also pineapple chunks.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve with brown rice.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add thawed strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Put half of mixture in dish. Refrigerate until firm.
Put sour cream over mixture and add remaining jello mixture and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into serving size squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: scramble egg surprise
directions: Scramble eggs.
When yellow, tear cheese and add them. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese in cubes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer in crock-pot approximately 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: gingerbread waffles
directions: Chill bowl and beater blades, then whip cream.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and place in refrigerator.
Prepare gingerbread mix according to package directions.
Heat waffle iron to desired temperature and add oil to griddle.
Spoon desired portions of gingerbread onto waffle griddle and cook until done.
Place cooked waffles in warm oven.
Serve warm with a spoonful of whipped cream and chopped walnuts on top.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix flour and cinnamon.
Mix carrots and butter.
Add flour mixture with baking powder.
Beat eggs separately and add to carrot mixture.
Then add vanilla.
Bake in 2-quart casserole at 350° for 15 minutes.
Then bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese paska
directions: Rub the cheese through a fine sieve.
Add a pinch of salt, the raisins, citron and almonds.
Soften the butter and combine with the sugar, stirring until the mixture is smooth.
Add the egg yolks and continue stirring.
Combine this with the cheese mixture, adding the whole egg which has been beaten until light and lemony.
Whip
the cream and stir it in.
Heat over a very low fire, stirring constantly just until bubbles form at the edges of the pan.
Remove from the fire and continue to stir while the mixture cools.
Add the vanilla extract and mold in wooden mold or flowerpot lined with wax paper or gauze.
Place a weight on top and be sure there is an opening for excess moisture to drain off.

title: sauerkraut sausage balls
directions: Strain and chop sauerkraut.
Cook sausage and onion; drain and mix with chopped sauerkraut and remaining ingredients.
Chill. Roll into balls.
Dip in flour, then egg mixture, and finally, breadcrumbs.
Deep fry.
May be reheated in the oven until hot.

title: custard filling
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Stir with a wire whisk until well blended.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Stir in orange extract. Stir in coconut; let cool.

title: old fashioned strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook until clear, stirring constantly. Add jello. Stir well.
Let cool. Add strawberries. Pour into pie shell. May be topped with whipped cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in a very small amount of salted water. Add oleo and cheese and let melt; add mayonnaise and beaten egg. Mix well and pour into a buttered casserole dish. Add lightly buttered bread crumbs. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: kolacky
directions: Thoroughly blend butter, cheese and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Knead to form stiff dough.
Roll 1/4-inch thickness on a well floured board.
Cut into 2-inch circles.
Place 1/4 teaspoon preserves in center.
Press together. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove and cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: First spread bean dip in the bottom of a rectangular pan. Then mix guacamole with juice from 1/2 lemon and salt and pepper to taste.
Spread over bean dip.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in tepid water.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add boiling water and salt; mix thoroughly.
Add beaten egg. Alternately add flour and yeast mixture.
Cover and leave inside refrigerator overnight.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels and milk in a double boiler. Add pecans. Place by spoonfuls on buttered cookie sheet in refrigerator for 1 hour. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin. Dip caramels into this. If too thick, add more paraffin. Allow to cool after dipping.

title: golden corn stuffing bake
directions: Combine soup, celery, onion and stuffing.
In 9-inch greased pie plate, spoon stuffing mixture.
Arrange chicken over stuffing mixture; press lightly into stuffing.
Combine sugar, margarine and mustard; spread evenly over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.

title: warm artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in crock-pot until cheese is melted and dip is warm.
Excellent with tortilla chips.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan in a hot oven (375°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm with either a chocolate or lemon sauce.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit and set aside.

title: pear-cranberry relish
directions: Force fruit through
food
chopper, using coarse blade. Add sugar and ginger.
Refrigerate
several hours or overnight before serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: artichoke spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cook and drain spinach. Combine spinach, sour cream, garlic, and 1/2 stick melted butter. Add artichokes and combine.
Melt the other 1/2 stick of butter and mix with the stuffing.
Place spinach mixture in the casserole dish and top with stuffing mixture.
Bake in preheated oven 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain completely.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour in long baking
pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 35 minutes or until done (using custard doneness test).
You may use ham or bacon.
Also you can add various vegetables for variety. Excellent holiday or other family breakfast.

title: tomato soup surprise
directions: Dice all vegetables fine.
Put in separate bowls or piles. Shred cheeses, separate and put in bowls or piles.
Boil tomato soup, made with water only!
Each person puts whatever veggies or cheeses they like into their bowls and pour soup to fill.
Cooks all together in bowl.
Tomato Surprise!

title: mcgood sauce
directions: Stir ingredients together and put on hamburgers.

title: patty mae's chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in mixture of melted butter, pepper sauce and vinegar.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with package of dry dressing mix.
Bake for 25 or 30 minutes, until brown.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: margaret's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add salt, butter (or margarine), syrup and then pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: basil butter
directions: In food processor, chop basil.
Add butter, lemon juice and pepper.
Blend until smooth.
Drop by half tablespoons onto cookie sheet; freeze.
Remove.
Store in freezer bags.
Serve with favorite bread or use to flavor chicken, fish or vegetables.

title: susie's "old timey" cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and flour; mix well. Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 3 regular layers or 4 thin layers.

title: grow coal flowers
directions: Mix and stir the ingredients.
Half submerge a piece of coal or an old piece of brick.
Watch it carefully as it grows.
You may try dotting the coal or brick with food coloring for different colors.
This is a very old recipe.
It is something we used to do.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk
on high until mixture comes to a boil, boiling about 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, stirring well.
Put in buttered pan.

title: low-fat french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and small amount of flour.
Stir until smooth.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup flour on counter. Gradually stir in remaining flour.
Remove dough from bowl and knead in last of flour.
Knead until smooth.
Place in bowl sprayed with Pam and cover with a warm, damp cloth until doubled, about 30 minutes.

title: lois' chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, cocoa and eggs; add milk and thicken. Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Top with Cool Whip or meringue.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook and cool rice.
Add broccoli, butter and onion.
Stir in milk with soup and add to rice mixture.
Add all cheese except enough to sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Add remaining cheese to top of casserole the last 10 minutes.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Peel and grate zucchini.
Mix all ingredients, except jello, together; boil for 15 minutes.
Add jello; stir well.
Pour into jars and seal.
Makes 5 pints.

title: pork ala christa
directions: Cut the loin in thick slices and saut. Lay them side by side in a pan. Cut the apples and bananas in 3/4-inch slices and lay on top of meat. Mix tomato sauce, curry and cream; spread on top. Put cheese on top and bake in preheated 400° oven until brown.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg and add milk.
Pour into dry ingredients.
Stir until batter is smooth.
Pare apples and dice or slice very thin.
Add apples to batter and blend together.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep hot fat, 370° to 375°.
Fry until a golden brown on all sides.
Roll in 10x sugar.
Makes 12 to 15 fritters.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Drain beet juice into pan. Add vinegar, salt and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Pour over hard-boiled eggs.
Leave in pan.

title: coconut mousse
directions: A very light dessert, as white as snow, which is prepared the day before serving.

title: chicken enchiladas (easy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop chicken and green chilies together in chopper or food processor.
Soften tortillas in hot oil.
Put 2 or 3 tablespoons of chicken mixture on tortilla and top with grated cheese and chopped onion.
Roll tortilla and place in baking dish or pan with roll edge down.
Repeat until all enchiladas are made.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Put cake mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and spread to the edge (very sticky).
Put pumpkin mixture over cake mix.
Take 1/2 c. set aside and add 1/2 c. sugar and 2 tsp. cinnamon.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of pumpkin mixture.

title: bread pudding with whiskey sauce
directions: Break the bread into chunks and combine with the milk in a bowl.
When bread is softened, break it up further and let it soak until the milk is absorbed.

title: hungarian hot rolls
directions: Mix warm water, yeast and sugar and let stand 15 minutes until foams.
Add approximately 2 cups flour, egg and shortening to yeast mixture.
Then mix in 1 cup more flour and salt.
Add 2 to 4 cups flour to form soft dough. Coat dough with oil and let rise 3 to 4 hours.
Turn onto floured surface and knead gently.
Pinch off dough and roll into balls.
Put rolls in greased (oil) pan. Coat rolls with oil.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake in unpreheated oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: vanilla ice cream(for 6-quart hand or electric freezer.)
directions: Blend eggs, pudding and some of the milk.
Empty blender into freezer can.
Blend Dream Whip, salt, sugar and some of the milk. Empty into freezer can.
Blend evaporated milk, condensed milk and some of the milk.
Empty into freezer can.
Add half and half to freezer can and fill to line on can with milk.
Add vanilla. Refrigerate several hours before freezing according to freezer directions.
Less half and half and low-fat milk can be used.

title: tasty dinner rolls
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Add melted butter.
Add salt and most of the flour.
Beat with a wooden spoon until mixture is smooth and satiny.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth, adding a little flour, if necessary.
Divide dough in half.
Shape each half into a long loaf.
Cut each loaf into 6 even pieces.
Shape into oblong rolls. Place rolls in a greased pan, fairly close to each other.
Slash tops.
Flatten slightly with palm of hand.
Sprinkle with little flour.
Let rise for about 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° on middle rack of oven for about 15 minutes or until light and golden brown. Makes 12 rolls.

title: sweet potato-apple casserole
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch slices. Boil until fork-tender. Cook apples in a little water. Reserve water. Butter a baking dish and add potatoes and apples in alternate layers. Mix honey, apple water and cinnamon. Pour over potatoes and apples. Dot with butter. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ham 'n' potatoes au gratin
directions: In a skillet, saute onions and green pepper in 1 tablespoon of margarine until tender.
Combine onions and pepper with potatoes, ham and mayonnaise; pour into an ungreased 9x13 baking dish.
In a saucepan, melt remaining margarine.
Stir in flour and pepper until smooth.
Gradually add milk and bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 1 minute.
Stir in cheese just until melted and pour over potato mixture.

title: very easy individual cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350F.
Place vanilla wafers in muffin tins. Cream together cream cheese, eggs and vanilla fill muffin tins halfway with cream cheese mixture.
Bake 10 minutes at 350F.
Top with fruit (cherries, blueberries, pineapple etc.) when cooled. Makes 24.

title: hot cranberry christmas punch
directions: Heat the 1 quart of water with sugar, cloves, cinnamon stick and red hots long enough to melt the red hots.
Add the cranberry juice, frozen orange juice and lemonade along with the 5 quarts of water.
Heat completely to serve.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, flour, sugar and salt in bowl; stir in egg whites and extract.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until brown around edges.
Remove from sheet at once.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: I put bread on jelly then peanut butter then put it in the microwave for 2 minutes - then put it in the oven for 3 minutes. Then back in the microwave for 10 minutes.
Then in the oven for 5 minutes.
Now a big glump in my mouth and it's all gone.

title: salad
directions: Mix together very thoroughly and chill.

title: german style green beans
directions: Saute bacon in a 1-quart saucepan over low heat until crisp. Add chopped onion; saute until tender.
Add bouillon granules, pepper and flour to bacon and onion; mix well.
Heat beans; drain, adding juice to bacon mixture.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour bacon mixture over beans, adding pieces of crisp bacon.

title: dandelion wine
directions: Boil dandelion flowers and water for 20 minutes, then strain. Add sugar, orange and lemon slices and boil for another 20 minutes.
Let cool.
When almost cold, add yeast cake.
Let ferment for a week; strain again.
Pour into bottles; leave open for 8 weeks.

title: onion cheese supper bread
directions: Cook onion in small amount hot fat until tender, but not brown.
Combine egg and milk.
Add to biscuit mix.
Stir only until mix is just moistened.
Add onion, half the cheese and parsley.
Spread dough in greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round cake pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Drizzle melted butter over.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Perfect salad go-with.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain juice from beets into a saucepan.
Add the salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Heat juice just to boiling point.
Put beets into a dish deep enough to keep submerged.
Pour hot liquid over beets.
Turn occasionally to let juice permeate all.
Let beets stand until reach room temperature, then put in refrigerator to chill.
Save the juice after beets are gone, in lidded jar in refrigerator to use again.
Serves 4.

title: jello salad
directions: Boil pineapple; add jello.
Stir until well mixed.
Add other ingredients, folding in Cool Whip last.
Chill and serve.

title: classic potato salad
directions: In large bowl stir together first 5 ingredients until smooth. Add remaining ingredients and toss to coat.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients well and place in 2 small or 1 large casserole dish.
Put slivered almonds evenly over vegetable mixture.
Crush crackers; add melted oleo and mix well.
Top the casserole with the cracker mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish with margarine.
Place layer of cracker crumbs in bottom of dish.
Layer with asparagus.
Mix cheese with soup and liquid from asparagus.
Place on top of asparagus and top with remaining or additional Ritz cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Line casserole dish with flour tortillas.
Top with layer of chicken, then layer of chopped onion and bell pepper.
Add layer of cheeses.
Mix soup with Ro-Tel tomatoes and pour over casserole.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan crunch cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 8 to 9 minutes at 325°.

title: favorite holiday chicken
directions: Mix
orange juice, rind and brown sugar.
Mix margarine with mustard
and
rub over chicken.
Place chicken, skin side down, in a greased baking pan and pour the juice mixture over all.	Bake at	425°
for 45 minutes until tender.
Baste frequently.
For the
last
15 minutes turn chicken to brown and glaze.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients into glass baking dish.
Microwave on High for 2 or 3 minutes or until butter is melted. Stir until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into buttered 8-inch pan. Cut into squares when cool.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients and form balls.
Put balls into 10 x 15-inch pan.
Prepare sauce, using chili sauce, jelly, lemon juice and 1/4 cup water.
Pour sauce over balls and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serve in a chafing dish.

title: punch
directions: Put sherbet or ice cream into a 2-gallon punch bowl.
Add juices and soda; stir lightly.
Makes 40 or more glasses.

title: tomato basil soup
directions: Preheat the broiler.

Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil. Lay 6 of the pepper halves, cut side down, on the foil and broil 2 inches from the heat until well charred, 5 to 10 minutes. Transfer the peppers to a plastic bag and seal the bag.
Allow the peppers to steam in the bag for 10 minutes.
Then remove them from the bag and slip off and discard the skins.
Coarsely chop the peppers and set aside.

title: coconut pound cake(low calorie)
directions: Mix all ingredients except cooking spray.
Pour mixture into a Bundt pan sprayed with cooking vegetable spray.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Cool on rack.

title: green pepper burgers
directions: Mix beef, chopped onion and egg.
Shape into big patties. Brown in oil.
Add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and ginger. Cook 1/2 hour, covered.
Slice green pepper over and cook 1/2 hour longer.

title: stuffed mushroom parmesan
directions: Twist out stems from mushrooms; wash stems and mushroom caps. Mince stems.
Melt butter in a skillet to foaming; add bay leaf. Saute until a golden brown.
Add mushroom caps and saute, covered, until they draw their water.
Place caps in a shallow baking dish or pie plate and keep at room temperature.
Discard bay leaf.
Add stems and garlic to skillet; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add parsley, ham, egg, pinch of oregano, sherry and enough cream or broth to make a smooth stuffing.
Add salt and Tabasco to taste; mix well.
Stuff the mushroom caps.
Sprinkle caps with Parmesan cheese.
Broil about 5 inches from flame until hot and golden brown (8 to 14 minutes).
Serve immediately.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Prepare rice as on package.
In small bowl, mix flour, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Put rice on bottom of greased bowl with margarine.
Put raw hamburger and diced onion on top of prepared rice.
Put a spoon of the flour mixture on top of hamburger.
Add can of stewed tomatoes, another spoon of flour mixture and finally add can of corn.
Bake in oven at 350°
for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: lime peach delight salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in usual way.
Let Jell-O cool and just begin to partially thicken.
Then stir in cabbage and pineapple with juice and chill until firm.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: *Can use diet oleo.

title: pea and peanut salad
directions: Make dressing by mixing together all ingredients except peas and peanuts.
In separate bowl break apart frozen peas and mix with peanuts.
Pour dressing over peas and nuts.
Mix gently until all are covered.
Cover and chill.

title: scott's clam chowder
directions: Drain clams into measuring cup.
Add boiling water to equal three cups.
In large pan, place potatoes, sauce mix and liquid. Heat to boiling.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Stir in clams, milk and margarine and heat through.

title: crabmeat hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix together.
Spread on split English muffins.
Cut into quarters; freeze.
Cook under broiler until bubbly and crisp, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: noodle lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together; drain.
Add oregano, basil, tomato juice and tomato paste; simmer.
Fix egg noodles according to package directions; drain.
Mix noodles, cottage cheese and sauce together and pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Layer Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potato casserole(serves 12 to 16)
directions: Place thawed potatoes in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Combine next 7 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed cornflakes and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be frozen.
Don't let flavor combination scare you, it's delicious!

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix all together well.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° until firm. Add meringue and bake at 425° until brown.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine the box of Lipton onion soup and hamburger.
Roll into about 3 inch meatballs.
Place in baking pan and bake in 350° oven until brown (about 20 minutes).
Take out of oven and mix the two cans of soup with 2 cans of water, then pour the mixture over the meat.
Return to oven for 45 minutes.

title: cocoa crispies
directions: Melt butter and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo until clear.
Add broccoli, soup, Cheez Whiz and chicken.
Mix well.
Stir in rice.
Simmer 5 minutes. Bake in casserole dish 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute chopped vegetables in butter until soft.
Blend in flour.
Add other ingredients with shrimp and cook 20 minutes.

title: mock swiss steak
directions: Shape meat into patties.
Fry until cooked.
Season as desired.
Drain fat as necessary.

title: caterbury sandwiches
directions: Spread bottom half of roll with horseradish sauce.
Fill other half with cheese, tomato and meat.
Yields 2 dozen.
Serve chilled.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl stir eggs, sugar, corn syrup, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in 350° oven 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on rack.

title: lunch box cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and chocolate chips.
Blend on low speed of mixer.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan that has been greased and floured. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top before baking.

title: bulgur cabbage salad(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Combine cracked wheat and warm water; let stand 1 hour.
Drain well.
Stir in cabbage and peas.
Mix together olive oil, lemon juice and dill.
Stir into cracked wheat.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: "philly" miracle whip wreath
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Place drinking glass in center of serving platter.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of mixture around glass to form ring, just touching outer edge of glass.
Smooth with spatula.
Remove glass.
Garnish with chopped parsley and pimento just before serving, if desired. Serve with wafers.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Place chicken on crescent roll, roll up and place in a baking dish.
Mix soup and broth and pour over rolls.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake at 350 degree until rolls are brown, approx. 30 minutes.

title: easy fruit punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with water; add
pineapple juice and fruit cocktail; mix thoroughly.

title: christmas snowballs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir flour, salt and nuts together.
With hands, work in flour mixture until dough holds together.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not brown.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool.
Roll in sugar again.
Makes about 4 dozen 1-inch cookies.

title: water chestnuts wrapped in bacon
directions: Heat ketchup and sugar in small pot over medium heat, stirring until caramelized.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: marinated tenderloin
directions: Sprinkle meat with garlic salt and red and black pepper. Combine olive oil, vinegar, Burgundy and garlic; stir well.
Pour over meat.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 425°; do not drain marinade.
(Bake at 140° for rare or 160° for medium.)
Yield: 20 to 24 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a mixing bowl, beat the shortening and margarine or butter with an electric mixer on medium or high speed for 30 seconds.
Add about one-half of the flour, the brown sugar, granulated sugar, eggs, vanilla and baking soda.
Beat mixture until thoroughly combined.
Beat in the remaining flour. Stir in chocolate pieces and, if desired, nuts.

title: country fried potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes as if for French fries.
Combine onions, potatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook in skillet with 2 tablespoons shortening or bacon drippings, which have been heated. Cover skillet while cooking.
After potatoes start cooking, add 1/2 cup of water and let steam until done.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Heat juices and dissolve Jell-Os into it.
Mix pineapple, cream cheese, nuts and cherries.
Add to Jell-O mixture (blend well).
Add 7-Up and pour into mold.
Let set for a few hours.

title: christmas cherries
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten egg yolk, vanilla, orange and lemon rind and lemon juice and mix well.
Add flour. Chill.
Roll into small balls 1/2-inch in diameter.
Roll in slightly beaten egg whites, then in chopped nuts.
Place on cookie sheet and press on a small piece of candied cherry.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Put all ingredients, except vanilla, in upper double boiler. Mix well by beating with beater.
Cook 7 minutes over boiling water.
Icing is done when it stands in peaks.
Remove from stove.
Add vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: enchilada pie casserole
directions: Fry the first 3 ingredients together.
Add the tomato sauce. Boil the potatoes.
Add the chili powder and the potatoes to the meat mixture.
Simmer.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef tenderloin across grain in 1/4-inch thick strips. In skillet, heat cooking oil.
Quickly brown the meat in oil for 2 to 4 minutes.
Remove meat from skillet.
Add sliced mushrooms and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove mushrooms.
Add sherry and beef broth to skillet and bring to a boil.
Cook, uncovered, until liquid is reduced to 1/3 cup.
Stir in dairy sour cream.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix milk, pepper, salt, bread and hamburger together and form into balls.
Place in large baking dish.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 6 (dry) ingredients in a bowl.
In another bowl mix last 6 ingredients.
Mix all together.
Grease pans (3 small loaves).
Bake at 350°for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: sollie's cornmeal muffins
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix thoroughly. Grease the muffin pan well.
Fill each muffin ring and bake at 425° until done.

title: meringue
directions: Mix egg whites, cream of tartar and vanilla.
When egg whites begin to froth, begin adding sugar.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar per egg white.
Beat until soft peaks form.
Put on pie and brown in oven on broil.

title: pork chop potato bake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam.
Put sliced potatoes in pan.
Place pork chops on potatoes.
Cover with can of cream of mushroom soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Place sugar, corn syrup, water, salt and peanuts in a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl or casserole dish.
Cook on High 5 minutes, then stir.
Cook on High an additional 13 to 15 minutes or until syrup reaches hard crack stage (300° on candy thermometer).
Stir in margarine or butter, baking soda and vanilla, just until light and bubbly.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet; spread.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix milk, egg, butter and corn.
Stir in dry ingredients, mix well.
Drop by spoonful into hot oil, (350°) fry until golden brown.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown onion and meat.
Add corn and seasonings.
Blend tomatoes with enchilada sauce.
Pour over meat mixture and 1/2 of sauce.
Simmer.
Add 1/2 cheese.
Alternate tortilla and meat mixture.
Spread cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cereal crunch
directions: Mix well.
Then melt one block of white Candi Quick.
Pour over cereal.
Spread out on tinfoil.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: tangier island corn pudding
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: all american baked beans
directions: (Or substitute above beans with 1 lb. dried beans, soaked.)

title: cheese loaf
directions: Place the cheeses into a large mixing bowl and allow it to become to room temperature.
Mix well, adding nuts, garlic powder and salt.
Put all of the mixture onto a large piece of wax paper and shape into a log.
Roll in chili powder and then wrap the log in foil.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with your choice of breads or crackers and garnish with parsley.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and serve.
Best with Chicken in a Biskit crackers.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In skillet, brown beef, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Add soup, water, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Heat thoroughly, stirring often.
Serve on buns.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In 2-quart casserole, place chocolate and butter; cover. Microwave at Medium or Low 5 to 7 minutes until chocolate and butter can be stirred smooth.
Add marshmallows and nuts, blending well.
Spread evenly in greased 8-inch square dish or pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut in squares.
Makes about 25 squares.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables by package directions and drain.
Add soup, mayonnaise, celery, onion, chestnuts, cheese and 1/2 of the cracker crumbs.
Save 1/2 the cracker crumbs to spread on top. Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sugar-free chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, using electric mixer, medium speed, combine ingredients as listed, adding the mayonnaise until you have firm, moist, smooth dough.
Remove beaters.
Work in nuts and candy bar crumbs by hand.
Shape into 120 small balls of equal size, using about a teaspoon of dough for each ball.
Place 1 1/2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes or until firm to touch and golden brown.
Makes 120 cookies at 45 calories each.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Add ingredients and refrigerate until set.

title: oatmeal refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well, and then add the rest. Shape into long rolls about 2 1/2 inches around. Chill several hours or overnight. Cut into slices with sharp knife. Place on an ungreased pan and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into thin slices.
Season with salt and pepper. Melt butter or margarine in large skillet.
Brown meat, mushrooms and onions.
Mix flour and evaporated milk.
Add to meat.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add Sauterne.
Serve over buttered noodles. Serves 4 to 6.

title: taco sauce
directions: Throw altogether into blender and blend.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Combine Catalina dressing, apricot preserves and dry onion soup mix.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken and bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: opal collins pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Add flour alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour. Add soda and extract. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken; remove meat from bones and chop.
Add all other ingredients to chicken and stir well.
Put in a casserole dish and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need an 8-inch plastic flowerpot and foil.

title: liz's tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook noodles.
Heat soup and milk.
Add cheese.
Stir until cheese melts and add to rest of casserole.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill before serving.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients
together.
Put head of cabbage in a large kettle of boiling water until leaves are softened.
Put balls of mixture in cabbage leaves and secure with toothpicks.

title: jill's meat loaf
directions: Note: Leftover pasta can be added, if available, however much you have and whatever shape you have.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Place all vegetables in boiling water.
Cook until tender. Mash a few vegetables for thickness, then add milk gradually.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add butter if desired.
Serves 2.

title: bread and butter pudding(taken from an english magazine, very good!)
directions: Butter pie dish.
Spread the bread with butter, remove the crust and cut into triangles.
Fill the dish with alternate layers of bread and currants.

title: angel food cake pie
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces in square dish with lid. Add Cool Whip and mix with cake. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together and add to cake mixture. Add cherry pie filling on top. Chill.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in half and slice into small pieces (shredded). Place oil in skillet.
Add all ingredients into pan and fry on medium heat until well done.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May add more buttermilk if too thick.
Bake in greased pan until brown.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift first 9 ingredients together.
Add raisins and nuts and toss to coat.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add an egg one at a time and mix well.
Add flour mixture alternately with applesauce.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 50 minutes or until done.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in bowl.
Make well in center. Combine eggs, buttermilk and margarine; mix well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Spoon into greased or papered muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 400°. Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic in large skillet; drain off grease.
Add chilies, tomato paste and cream of mushroom soup; mix well.
Layer bottom of 9 x 12-inch cake pan with half the tortilla chips.
Cover chips with hamburger mixture.
Add another layer of tortilla chips.
Cover chips with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until boiling.

title: pumpkin pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Gradually add remaining ingredients (stir between each item).
Fill each unbaked crust with half of mix. Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 375° and bake 50 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: seven layer mexican dip
directions: Layer beans, avocados, sour cream, tomatoes, green onions, black olives and Cheddar cheese in a 9 x 13-inch dish in order listed.
Chill overnight.
Serve with your favorite chips or crackers.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place all ingredients in bowl.
Mix thoroughly by hand about 50 strokes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
(This is a very moist cake.)

title: mrs. johnson's cocoa recipe
directions: Mix together.
To use, fill cup 1/2 full of mix and fill with hot water.

title: strawberry blintz torte
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon of salt. Combine shortening and 1/2 cup of sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Beat egg yolks until thick; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in milk and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Spread in two 8-inch cake pans.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon; drain and save 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook 1/2 cup chopped onions in drippings. Stir in one can cream of potato soup, one can of clams (undrained) and 1/2 cup milk.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix together well.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan; cut into small squares.

title: sunflower
directions: Cook ground beef patty and place on hamburger bun on a dinner plate.
Pour hot chili over patty and bun.
Spread lettuce over entire plate.
Sprinkle tomato, onion and cheese on top of lettuce.
Salt to taste.
Place your choice of chips around edge of plate. Makes one serving.

title: bird feed
directions: Add peanut butter to hot, melted shortening.
Mix well.
Add cornmeal, a little at a time.
Try to get it not too sticky nor too crumbly.
Shape and hang in onion sack for feeder.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Immerse cabbage leaves in boiling water for about 3 minutes; set aside to drain.
Saute chopped cabbage and minced onion in butter until tender.
Add rice, cheese, salt and pepper.
Divide mixture among cabbage leaves.
Fold in sides and roll to enclose filling; fasten with toothpicks.
Place rolls in a single layer in a shallow saucepan.
Add tomato juice; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat, stir in marshmallows, chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute or until marshmallows melt and blend.
Pour into 8-inch square buttered dish.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over crushed cereal in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips over low heat in small saucepan, stirring constantly.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes or until firm.
Cut into squares. Yield:
40 servings.

title: easy jello whip
directions: Gently combine all ingredients; refrigerate until well chilled.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar and turmeric; bring to boil.
Pour over grated cabbage and other ingredients.
It's better if made day before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: party spaghetti
directions: Heat oil; cook meat brown with onions.
Stir in Prego sauce, parsley flakes and oregano and cook approximately 15 minutes. Combine cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Blend well. Layer spaghetti, sauce and cheese mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Toast bread and layer in a large, buttered casserole dish. Brown sausage and drain.
Add onion, green pepper and green onions and saute.
Layer sausage mixture on bread.
Beat eggs, milk and pepper, then pour over first 2 layers.
Add layer of sour cream and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie(1 pie)
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together.
Then add remaining ingredients and cook 1 hour on medium heat.

title: 9 minute caramel popcorn
directions: Cook
brown
sugar, Karo syrup and butter on High power for
3 minutes.
Stir
and
cook	for 3 more minutes or until boiling. Add salt and soda and stir.
Put popcorn and mixture into a big brown
paper
sack and cook in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Take out
and shake bag good; cook for 1 1/2 minutes long and reshake bag.
Pour	out
into a bowl.
Make sure you shake the bag until mixture has coated all popcorn.

title: peg's dessert
directions: Melt butter and mix in flour and pecans.
Spread evenly in bottom of 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Whip together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 cups Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk; spread over cheese mixture.
Cover with 1/2-inch of Cool Whip.
Grate almond Hershey bar and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate or freeze until firm.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll biscuits until thin.
Cut in half.
Use 1/4 apple.
Roll in biscuit half.
Place in baking dish, cut side down, close but not touching.
Using a saucepan, mix sugar, margarine, water, lemon juice and pie spices.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over apples and biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together to bake in a tube pan lined with paper greased on both sides.
Pack tight into pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Cool and wrap in foil and refrigerate for 2 or 3 days before slicing.
This cake will even freeze well.
Cake is very pretty to use red and green candied fruit.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Blend in paraffin.
Mix confectioners sugar, milk and vanilla in bowl.
Shape by spoonfuls into balls around cherries.
Dip into chocolate to coat.
Place into airtight container.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: nacho dip
directions: Saute sausage until done/drain well.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and just enough taco sauce to change the color and make it your first layer.
Sprinkle the sausage over the cream cheese for your 2nd layer.
Shred lettuce and cheese.
Put your shredded lettuce over the sausage.
Sprinkle the chop onions, and sliced olives and chopped tomatoes over the shredded lettuce.
Sprinkle the shredded cheese (cheddar or your choice) over the onions all placed on a 9x13.
Pour the remaining taco sauce over the top and refrigerate until 1 hour before serving.
Preheat oven to 300, bake until cheese is melted and warm.
Serve with tacos.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix, bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Pour in small crock-pot.
Serve with crackers.
Very good with rye crackers.

title: monkey bread
directions: Syrup:
Bring 1 cup sugar, 2 sticks margarine and 1 teaspoon cinnamon to a boil.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon in shaker bag.
Cut biscuits into quarters in the bag.
Place in ungreased tube pan 2 cans biscuits and 1/2 syrup, then 2 cans biscuits and 1/2 syrup.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes on lowest rack.
Cool 5 minutes, then turn over.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler.
When melted add sugar, milk and cornstarch which have already been blended with water.
Remove from double boiler and place on direct heat, medium-high.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Stir. Enjoy!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 5 minutes. Drain well.
Put butter and cheese into broccoli while hot and let melt.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Crush 1 stack of Ritz crackers (from a 12 ounce box).
Mix with 1 stick melted butter and spread over top of casserole.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease tube pan.
Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Shake in bag with 3/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Put layer of cherries, pecans and half the biscuit dough.
Then top with rest of biscuit dough in tube pan.
Mix 1 cup brown sugar and oleo. Pour over cake.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and ham quiche
directions: Line pan with pastry and partially bake, unfilled, for 20 minutes in a 425°
oven.
Remove stems from broccoli; cut tops in small pieces and blanch in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes. Drain, cool and chop coarsely (about 2 cups).
Whisk together cream, milk and eggs; add broccoli, ham, cheese and wine vinegar. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into pastry shell and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 375°
oven for 30 minutes until puffed and brown on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well. Pour into 2-quart casserole. Top with crumbled Ritz crackers and butter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour the boiling water over the oatmeal and let stand 20 minutes. Cream the shortening, brown sugar, white sugar and eggs. Add oatmeal to this mix.
Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to first mix.
Add the nuts, if desired.
Bake in oblong pan 35 minutes at 350°.
Do not cool to put topping on.

title: candy cookies
directions: Mix together in 3-quart pan all ingredients, except oats. Boil for 2 minutes at hard boil, stirring constantly.
Drop on wax paper and flatten.
Let cool completely and store in airtight container.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in butter until golden.
Blend in flour and seasoning.
Cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat. Gradually add milk; bring to boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add corn and egg.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish; top with Ritz crackers (crushed).
Dot with butter.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Boil brown sugar, butter, syrup, and salt 5 minutes. Remove from heat; add baking soda and butter flavoring. Pour and stir over popcorn and nuts. Place in 200° oven for 1 hour. Remove and cool completely. Store in covered container to keep crisp.

title: tomato relish
directions: Peel tomatoes and chop them up.
Add all the other ingredients and stir up good.
Cook on low heat 40 to 50 minutes.
Put in jars while hot and seal.
This is good with most all kinds of vegetables.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cook broccoli in boiling salted water; don't overcook.
Drain.
Arrange in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place sliced chicken pieces on broccoli.
Combine chicken soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of mixture, then combine melted margarine and bread crumbs.
Stir together, then put on top of cheese.
I use loaf bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: sour cream date delights
directions: Sift flour with dry ingredients; cream butter and sugar; add egg and vanilla flavoring.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Fold in chopped dates and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen cookies.

title: alitcha fit pit (ethiopia)
directions: Spread croutons in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cook sausage until brown; drain well and sprinkle over croutons. Combine eggs and next 4 ingredients.
Mix well and pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and let stand 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: shrimp and spaghetti(30 minute preparation)
directions: Heat olive oil in electric skillet at 250°.
Place onion rings and pressed garlic clove in heated oil.
Cover, but stir frequently, until rings begin to turn transparent.
Immediately turn heat down to warm and add shrimp.
Stirring frequently, cook shrimp in onions until shrimp is done (turns from grey to pink). Remove and spoon mixture into cooked spaghetti noodles.
Great served with buttered garlic bread.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches, sugar, flour and cook until tender.
Remove from fire and add oleo and vanilla.
Pour into baking dish.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip, well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Chill 2 hours.

title: peach crunch
directions: Arrange peaches in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Pour 1/4 cup of liquid over peaches.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over peaches.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until topping is golden brown.
Serve with whipped cream or half and half, as desired.

title: fudge
directions: Combine milk, margarine and sugar in heavy pan and cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Stir often! Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish and chill until firm.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of dry cake mix over margarine.
Spread drained peaches on top. Spread rest of dry cake mix on top.
Mix syrup with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: magical coconut pie
directions: In beater
bowl,
beat	eggs
until light, then add and beat sugar until thick;	add milk gradually as you beat.
Sift together flour,
salt
and
baking
powder
and
beat in.
Add margarine, vanilla
and coconut and beat into mix.
Butter two 8-inch pie plates and pour mixture evenly into them.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set and top is a beautiful gold. (Forms its own crust, filling and top.)

title: hot sweet potato salad
directions: *You may need more if potatoes are dry.

title: company crab mousse
directions: Lightly oil a 4-cup mold.
In small saucepan over low heat, combine soup, cream cheese and gelatin; stir until mixture is smooth and creamy, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into prepared mold.
Cover; chill several hours until firm.
To serve, invert mold onto lettuce-lined serving plate.
Serve with thinly sliced snack bread, crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: rice pudding
directions: Add rice, sugar and salt in large cooking pot.
Add milk, bring to boil then simmer until rice is tender.
Stir often.
Beat eggs and add the cup of milk
to it.
Add rice mixture, bring to boil again and remove from heat immediately.
Pour into large bowl and let cool.
Chill.
Stir often.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and cook to soft ball stage, 236° on candy thermometer.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Stir until thick and grainy.
Turn onto waxed paper at once and quickly separate nuts.

title: chicken hash
directions: In food grinder, chop chicken, onion, potatoes and carrots. Mix well with remaining ingredients.
Place in slow cooker on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo in a saucepan, mixing well over low heat and bring to a boil 1/2 to 1 full minute.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Add oats, stir quickly and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: stuffed steak
directions: Cut round steak into 3 x 4-inch pieces.
Chop bacon and onion into small pieces.
Put bacon and onion inside steak and roll the steak up.
Secure the steak with a toothpick.
Brown the steak rolls on stove top.
Place in a baking pan.
Cover with can of mushroom soup.
Bake in 275° oven for 2 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish.

title: steak san marco
directions: In large skillet, arrange meat and cook in oil until brown. After browning meat, add onion soup mix and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with oregano, garlic powder, pepper and vinegar.
Cover and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and white corn syrup until hard boil stage. Pour hot mixture into stiffly beaten egg whites; continue beating on high speed of mixer.
Add vanilla and powdered sugar.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour onto marble.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Melt butter, Karo syrup and water. Add remaining ingredients. Drop off by 1/2 tablespoon for each cookie.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Makes a big and thin cookie.

title: hearty cabbage and beans
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add Prosciutto, garlic and onion.
Cook over moderately high heat until onion is softened and translucent (about 3 to 5 minutes).
Add hot pepper and stir for 30 seconds.
Add cabbage and mix well.

title: caramel-chocolate squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Heat caramels and 1/4 cup of the milk in saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth. Keep mixture warm over low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: oriental barbecue wings
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over wings.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain and save juice from clams.
Mix liquids and cream cheese until smooth.
Add clam juice until desired consistency is reached.
Stir in clams.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken provencale
directions: Brown chicken over moderate heat in a 12-inch skillet lightly coated with cooking spray for 5 minutes on each side.
Set aside in a large bowl.
Add olive oil, onion and garlic to skillet; cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring.
Add pepper and cook for 5 minutes.
Transfer to bowl with chicken.
Raise heat to moderately high and cook eggplant for 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir until golden.

title: low fat yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip together; pour into pie crust. Refrigerate 2 or more hours or overnight.
You can slice strawberries and put on top of pie or sprinkle blueberries on top. Delicious!

title: pumpkin stew
directions: Brown stew beef and onions.
Pressure cook in 2 cups bouillon for 1/2 hour.
Depressurize.
(This is best done a day ahead and refrigerated so extra fat can be skimmed off.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain in saucepan.
Mix cheese, milk and soup over low heat.
Add to broccoli mixture in casserole dish. Top with almonds or buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: southwest cheesecake
directions: In a mixer, beat together cream cheese and Cheddar cheese until fluffy.
Add 1 cup sour cream.
Add the taco seasoning; beat until mixed.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Fold in green chiles. Spoon into a well-greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 34 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Add remaining cup of sour cream to top of cheesecake.
Bake 5 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate overnight.
Remove sides from the pan and place on a serving platter.
Top with salsa, olives and green onions.
Serve with chips.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and dry Ranch dressing mix in a bowl.
Form 1 large or several small balls.
Roll in crushed almonds. Refrigerate until serving time.
Serve with Townhouse crackers.

title: lana's corn pudding
directions: Melt butter; add drained Niblets and creamed corn.
Lightly beat eggs and add to corn mixture.	Add sour cream, corn bread mix and Ranch dressing mix.
Bake in 2-quart dish for 45 minutes at 350°.
Can sprinkle cheese on top.

title: meal in foil
directions: Make large hamburger patties, enough for your family.
Season with salt and pepper. Top with onion slice, potatoes and carrots. Wrap in foil and seal. Bake at 425° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bread pudding with bourbon sauce
directions: Soak bread in milk until soft.
Combine sugar, vanilla, eggs and raisins in small bowl; whisk really well.
Add to bread mixture and stir gently.
Pour into buttered 9 x 12 glass casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350 degrees or until lightly browned and the consistency of thick, thick pudding. After removing from oven, sprinkle pecans on top.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix together chicken soup, mushroom soup, milk, onion and chili pepper. Add chicken and 1/2 cheese.
Butter large dish, 9 x 13-inches. Pour about 3/4 cup broth from chicken into dish, then arrange the following in layers:
1/2 of the tortillas and 1/2 of the soup mixture.
Repeat.
Cover with cheese and refrigerate several hours. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours covered.
Uncover the last 30 minutes. This takes a bit of preparation but is delicious!

title: salmon dip
directions: Combine all ingredients well and chill before serving.

title: crabmeat mornay dip
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and saute onion and parsley. Blend in flour, cream and cheese until cheese is melted. Add other ingredients and gently fold in crab meat. This may be served in a chafing dish with Melba toast or in pastry shell.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant 1/2 inch thick.
Parboil with salt until tender.
Alternate in a baking dish, a layer of eggplant, chicken and cracker crumbs.
Repeat until used.
Pour milk over all and top with crumbs and pepper.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Put shredded cheese on top the last 10 minutes.

title: corn meal muffins
directions: Combine melted butter and
sugar.
Stir
in beaten egg. Mix flour, corn meal, salt and	baking	powder	and add to egg mixture.
Add milk and mix	well.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.	Check with cake tester after 15 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Chop dates in food chopper.
Add nuts, soda, shortening and boiling water.
Mix together and let stand 15 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid (cut water by 1/2).
Add juice, ginger ale and stir.
Add in sherbet and stir until foamy.
Makes 32 servings.

title: german sauerbraten
directions: Place meat in a large glass or plastic bowl (non-metal) and add all ingredients listed. Add enough water to the bowl to cover the meat. Cover bowl with a lid or Saran Wrap, refrigerate and let meat marinate for 3 to 5
days.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Blend well with your hands.
Pack into a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven and let stand a few minutes before turning out.

title: pizza crust(for two pizzas)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add oil and sugar.
Gradually stir in flour until dough follows wooden spoon around bowl.
Turn out onto floured surface and knead with remaining flour.

title: vegetable pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, then drain. Combine pasta, tomato, cheese, salad dressing, orange juice, green onion, celery and olives.
Toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill. Toss with spinach just before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: oriental dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in sour cream, water chestnuts, scallions, sesame seed and soy sauce.
Chill 1 hour or until serving time.

title: bean chili with turkey italian sausage
directions: Follow directions on back of bean bag for soaking beans and cooking.
After beans are cooked, saute onion, garlic and sausage in a pan (I squeeze the sausage out of the casing), until meat is brown.
Add tomatoes, lemon and contents of chili packet.
Simmer 5 minutes, then add to bean pot.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: strawberry patch cake
directions: Break up cake into bite size pieces; reserve.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; add sliced strawberries and stir until they are separated.
Chill until thick and syrupy.
(Be sure this doesn't get too thick.)
Remove from refrigerator and fold in Cool Whip (save part for topping).
Grease a 9 x 10-inch tube pan or rind mold (use butter).
Put 2 cups cake pieces in pan, then add jello mixture.
Continue this until pan is full or all mixture is used. Chill several hours or overnight.
Sit pan in hot water for a second and turn out on plate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together first 12 ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Melt butter; pour over crushed corn flakes.
Add almonds.
Return to oven to brown.
This recipe may be frozen.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to a boil.
Let cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Remove from bones. Cut in bite size pieces.
Cream together soups and milk until smooth.
Add chicken. Mix the Stove Top mix and put on top of chicken in a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: good punch
directions: Mix juices and lemonade together in punch bowl.
Stir in ginger ale and ice when ready to serve.

title: grand champion pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 375°. Bake 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding, milk, frozen orange juice concentrate and sour cream.
Cut up fruit and drain cans.
Add to the milk mixture. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: royal cranberry salad
directions: On day before serving, grind cranberries and oranges; mix with sugar.
Let set overnight.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Mix jello and add gelatin mixture.
Add drained pineapple and nuts. Chill thoroughly.
Serves 15.

title: barbecued beans
directions: In a large pot add beans, sugar, mustard and soy sauce.
Heat over medium heat until sugar is melted.
Then add your browned ground meat and onion.
Let come to a boil and then turn it on low and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Great for picnics!!!

title: slaw
directions: Mix and refrigerate until ready to use. Cover.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Whisk pudding and milk together, fold in cool whip and set-aside.
Spray 9 x 13 inch pan with PAM.
Place layer of graham crackers in pan.
Spoon 1/2 of pudding mixture on 1st layer of crackers.
Repeat with another layer of crackers then remaining pudding mixture.
Cover with another layer of crackers. Refrigerate.

title: country-style sausage links
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Stir well.
Shape mixture into 12 links.
Place a large nonstick skillet over medium heat until hot.
Add half of sausage links and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until browned, turning frequently.
Drain well on paper towels. Repeat procedure with remaining links.
Yields 12 links.

title: yummy squares
directions: Put vanilla wafers in bottom of cake pan, enough to cover the whole bottom.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients, dividing filling equally into each pie crust.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: doggie biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. In medium bowl, dissolve bouillon in water. Add remaining ingredients, stirring until well blended.

title: macaroni and cheese with smoky sausages
directions: In oven, melt butter in baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch).
Add macaroni, salt and pepper; stir to coat macaroni with butter.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour milk over macaroni and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes on 350°.
Arrange sausage links on casserole.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until sausages are hot.
Yields 8 servings.

title: j.b.'s barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in order in medium size saucepan with heat on low to medium.
Simmer for 20 minutes with occasional stir to keep from sticking.
Add more lemon juice for tartness.
Excess can be saved for later use.
Store in refrigerator in sealed container.

title: chicken coating for oven fried chicken
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Spray pan with Pam or vegetable oil.
Rinse chicken and drain.
Dredge in flour mixture 1 piece at a time and arrange skin side up in prepared pan.
Melt 1/4 pound margarine. Apply in dabs with pastry brush (to drizzle won't work).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Remaining flour mixture may be saved.

title: congealed salad
directions: In three cups boiling water dissolve jello; dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/3 cup water.
Combine with jello, add marshmallows. Remove from stove and add crushed pineapple.
Put in refrigerator until nearly congealed.
Then fold in Cool Whip and nuts.

title: light banana pie
directions: Mix together pudding mix and milk with whisk until thick. Then spoon in half of Cool Whip with pudding mix and stir well. Pour into the pie crust.
Chill about 1 hour; then when serving, top with slices of bananas and a spoon of the remaining Cool Whip.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Note:
If honey is used, only 1/4 cup of milk should be used.

title: almond-spinach pilaf(serves 4)
directions: In a medium saucepan over medium heat, warm oil.
Add the spinach, scallions, dill, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring frequently until vegetables are tender, about 2 minutes.
Add the rice and almonds; cook, stirring constantly until rice is well coated with oil, about 2 minutes.
Pour in broth and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer until rice is tender, 20 minutes.
Gently stir in orange sections.

title: matthew's one dish dinner
directions: Brown
beef
and onion in skillet;
drain
grease.
Put mixture in 2-quart buttered casserole.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spread
vegetables
evenly
over
the
beef
mixture. Spread cheese soup evenly over the	vegetables.
Arrange Tater Tots over casserole to cover cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Finely chop drained shrimp and drained clams.
Add all other ingredients, except gelatin, to creamed mixture.
Mix gelatin with clam juice, then add to other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: banana bread(going nuts is optional.)
directions: Mash bananas well.
Add sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla; mix. Sift flour, baking soda and powder together and add to banana mixture.
Add margarine or butter in small quantities as you go. Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour; then increase to 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 medium loaves.

title: j & s sloppy joes
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion in the butter. Add the remaining ingredients. Simmer for 4 hours.

title: easy enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat with salt, pepper, garlic, onion, and green chilies. Drain excess fat.
Add soups and enchilada sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes to combine flavors.
If mixture is too dry, add a small amount of water.
Spray casserole pan with Pam.
Tear tortillas into bite sized pieces.
Cover bottom of pan.
Add 1/2 mixture. Add 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together with mixer.
Spread this mixture in a round large dish or pizza pan.
Cover with hamburger, cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and onions.
Dip with chips.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into pie crust and bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: larry's pumpkin cake
directions: *Be careful not to get pumpkin pie filling.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Beat on high speed until light and fluffy.
Blend in vanilla.

title: holiday wreath cookies
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows carefully.
Remove from stove. Add vanilla, food coloring and then cornflakes last.
Stir.
Keep hands moistened with water when forming small wreaths.
Put on wax paper.
Decorate with red cinnamon candies.
Don't pile on top of each other, they will stick together.

title: cowboy strawberry shortcake
directions: Cook
cake
as	directed
in a 13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch pan. When done, stick holes all over cake with a fork.
Mix Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups hot water and pour over cake.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes, then put strawberries and juice on top.
Top with the vanilla
pudding
mix and milk; mix well and fold in Cool Whip. Keep cake refrigerated.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar in saucepan.
Stir in pretzels. Spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until it bubbles.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick margarine.
Press into bottom of pan.
Place in fridge.

title: polish filled roll-up
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add sugar, shortening, salt and milk.
Add eggs and the yeast, mix thoroughly. Blend in flour, beating well after each addition.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place 15 minutes.
Toss on floured surface to coat dough with flour.
Roll out and spread with filling, starting at one edge and spreading to within 1/3 inch of other three edges.
Roll as for jelly roll, starting with the covered edge.
Seal.
Place on greased baking sheet, seam-side down.
Brush with cream and cover. Let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: english tea scones
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Mix dry ingredients.
