Cut butter into the dry ingredients, using a pastry blender until the mixture has a consistency of coarse meal. Mix in heavy cream just until the dough holds together. Wrap in wax paper or plastic and chill about 30 minutes.
Roll the chilled dough into a circle 1/2-inch thick.
Use a cookie cutter to cut dough into 40 scones.
Combine 1 egg and 1/4 cup light cream and brush the tops of the scones. Bake until golden brown and puffy, about 13 to 15 minutes.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: In a buttered casserole, arrange layers of potatoes, soup mixture and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: harvard beets
directions: Take and cook first 5 ingredients until thick.
Add beets and let stand 5 minutes or longer.
Just before serving, heat and add butter.

title: no fail fudge
directions: In 2-quart saucepan mix margarine, sugar and milk.
Add marshmallows and heat on high, stirring constantly until boiling. Turn down to medium and boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in chips until melted.
Add walnuts and pour into 9 x 10-inch pan that has been well buttered.

title: baked eggs
directions: Mix scrambled eggs, salt, sour cream and milk.
Top with 8 ounces shredded cheese and butter.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until set.
Can also top with crushed corn flakes.

title: whole wheat crumb crust
directions: Beat with beater until crumbly.
Pack into bottom of pie pan.

title: mock fig pickles
directions: Soak tomatoes in salt water 2 hours.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add tomatoes and cook slow over a low flame until tender (about 30 minutes).
Seal in jars while hot.

title: cheese strata
directions: Quarter bread and lay in an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch or 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Alternate layers of bread and cheese (usually 2 layers each), ending with cheese.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over bread and cheese.
Cover and chill overnight or at least 6 hours.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. When finished baking, let stand 30 to 45 minutes until firm, then serve.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Heat oil in a 4-quart pot.
Add onion, celery, carrots, bell pepper and garlic; saute 5 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Stir in flour and chili powder.
Add tomatoes with their liquid, broth and beans.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until beans and vegetables are tender and the liquid has thickened.
Adjust seasonings with salt and pepper, if desired.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: kid pleasing chili
directions: Heat oil in heavy pan.
Add onions, celery and garlic; cook 3 minutes.
Add turkey; cook, stirring to break up meat until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes with their liquid, broth, chili powder, cumin, salt, oregano and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add beans and corn.
Simmer 15 minutes more or until thickened.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and 3/4 cup water in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Increase heat and boil without stirring until syrup is crackly.
Beat egg whites stiff; pour syrup into whites.
Beat constantly.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Beat until mixture stands in peaks.

title: man's cake
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Mix with cake mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with topping mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Peel half of the zucchini.
Saute onion in oleo.
Combine zucchini, onion and chicken broth.
Cook together 30 minutes or until soft.
Season to taste.
Blend in blender.
Add about 1/2 cup milk.
May freeze before adding milk.

title: tiramisu(low fat)
directions: To assemble the desserts, coarsely crumble 1 1/2 ladyfingers into the bottom of each of six (10 oz.) balloon wine glasses.
Top the ladyfingers with 1 tablespoon of the coffee mixture, and 1/4 cup of the custard.
Repeat the layers.
Then sift a little cocoa over the top of each dessert.
Cover the desserts and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
If desired, top each serving with 2 tablespoons of the whipped topping just before serving.

title: "ship wreck"
directions: Peel
and
slice
potatoes
in
bottom
of well-greased 2-inch deep
casserole
dish.
Salt
and pepper to taste.
Add layer of carrots
and celery and then beans.
Brown onion and ground beef. Put on top then add tomato soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for
hours.
Uncover and let brown the last 15 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook all ingredients together for about 10 minutes until it thickens.
Cool and place in cooked pie shell.
Top with real or lite whipped cream.
Cook on low fire and stir continuously.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add baking powder, salt, soda, ginger and cinnamon.
Sift again.
Combine melted shortening, molasses and warm water.
Add well beaten egg and blend well.
Add the dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Roll out on a lightly floured board to 1/3-inch thickness and cut with a round cookie cutter.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: onion rings
directions: Separate onion into rings and place in ice water in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Mix together flour, oil, egg and water in a bowl.
Beat egg white until stiff.
Fold egg white into flour mixture.
Coat onion rings by dipping into mixture, then drop rings into hot Crisco.
Fry until golden brown.
Salt, if desired.

title: toad in a hole
directions: Cut 2-inch hole in center of bread.
Melt butter in skillet. Fry bread in skillet until golden brown.
Turn bread over and break egg into center hole.
Reduce heat and cook to desired doneness.
Salt and pepper.
May flip bread over if desired.

title: fudge pie
directions: Sift flour and cocoa together; add sugar and salt.
Add to beaten egg.
Add vanilla.
Fold in nuts and melted butter.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Serve with whipped cream or peppermint ice cream.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes with pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on one side. Remove chops as they brown; reserve drippings. Place half of potatoes in greased 9 x 13 pan. Top with cheese slices and then the remaining potatoes. Place pork chops, brown side up, on potatoes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cook onions in skillet until tender. Add soup and milk. Heat and pour over pork chops. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: brownie cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed on package.
Cool, stirring once or twice.
Stir in dry cake mix and blend well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts evenly over the top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill until ready to use.

title: cherry delight with pretzels
directions: Melt butter in pan, add sugar and mix well.
Add pretzels and mix well. (Keep 1 cup for topping.)
Put remainder in long casserole dish.
Fold cream cheese, powdered sugar and Dream Whip together, spread half of mixture on pretzels;
spread cherry pie filling over this and repeat.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Beat all together until light and fluffy. This goes good on a raisin cake and also on chocolate cakes.

title: pennsylvania dutch spiced beef casserole
directions: Brown beef cubes in electric frying pan.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper, sugar and spices and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Cook pasta separately and drain.
Add to first mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve.

title: hard candy apples
directions: In a saucepan, blend sugar, corn syrup and water.
Bring to a boil over high heat until mixture reaches 290°.
Remove pan from heat.
Allow to stand until bubbles have simmered down.
Add 8 to 10 drops of cinnamon oil and red food coloring as desired.
Dip apples on sticks in mixture; allow to cool on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.

title: reese's peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt oleo.
Add graham crackers, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake sweet potatoes in microwave oven.
Then peel and mash. Combine sweet potatoes with other main ingredients with hand mixer or food processor.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 400° until no longer soupy (approximately 1 hour, but depends on amount of mashed potatoes).

title: cottage noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Melt butter in saucepan; add onion and cook until clear.
Blend flour, mustard and salt; add to butter and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Remove from heat.
Blend in lemon juice and fold in cottage cheese.
Combine with drained noodles.
Pour mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese over top and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Place under broiler just long enough to brown the cheese on top.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a well-greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes, or until firm.

title: impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients in blender in order given.
Blend at high speed for 15 seconds.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not make a crust.

title: kurt's big weakness
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix well. Press dough into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate morsels.
Let stand until chocolate melts; spread evenly.

title: salsa bean salad
directions: Rinse and drain all beans.
Combine all beans, onions and green peppers in large bowl.
Combine salsa, salad dressing and salt. Add to bean mixture.
Stir lightly and chill.
Cover 4 to 24 hours, stirring often.
Stir in tomato just before serving.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: catfish stew and rice
directions: Combine water, potatoes, onion and garlic in large pot.
Cook on high heat for 15 minutes.
Lower heat.
Add cabbage, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add catfish.
Cook 15 minutes. Remove from heat.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no fail hash brown potatoes
directions: Grease baking dish.
Break apart hash browns.
Brown onion. Mix potatoes, sour cream, onion and Cheddar cheese.
Spread in baking dish.
Cut margarine into tablespoon slices and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until golden brown.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots.
Chop apples- 1 red and 1 green. Cut seedless grapes in half.

title: southern corn cakes
directions: Heat griddle slowly while mixing batter.
Beat egg well, then beat in rest of ingredients until smooth.
Spoon onto hot griddle. Makes 16.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients.
Mix together and stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill dough in refrigerator.
Roll into balls.
Dip each one into sugar.
Place sugared top up on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle each cookie with 2 or 3 drops of water. Bake until set, but not hard, for 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: nutty cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. In a medium bowl, stir together dry cake mix, butter and nuts. Press mixture evenly in bottom of pan.

title: easy corn chowder
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add canned tomatoes and diced potato.
Cook until tender, approximately 20 minutes. Add creamed corn and heat until hot.
Serve with crackers.

title: dumplings
directions: Bring water to a boil in sauce pan.
Stir in margarine until melted; remove from heat.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Roll 1/4 at a time to 1/8-inch thickness on lightly floured surface.
Cut into 1 inch squares. Bring broth to a boil in large sauce pan.
Drop dumplings into boiling broth.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until dumplings are tender.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: heart healthy pineapple cheesecake squares
directions: Set aside 2/3 cup of the pineapple juice.
Add remaining pineapple juice to unsweetened
orange juice to equal 1 cup.
In medium saucepan, combine the sugar, flour and pineapple/orange juice. Bring mixture to a boil, then stir for 1 minute or until mixture reaches pudding consistency.
Remove from heat, then fold in drained, crushed pineapple.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs, vanilla and sour milk. Blend.
Mix dry ingredients and blend with creamed mixture.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into greased and floured 9x13 inch pan. Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Roll into small balls or twist into half moons.
Bake at 350° until done or brown on bottom.
Cool completely.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Warm cookies will cause sugar to melt.

title: betty's chow chow
directions: * Two cups equal 1 pound.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pat out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° to 450° until brown.

title: simple salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix 3 minutes. Bake at 325° until done.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water 3 minutes. Cool, but do not drain. Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs. Stir in raisin mixture and vanilla. Sift all dry ingredients together; add to cream mixture. Mix well. Add nuts and chips. Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: homemade italian egg noodles
directions: Measure flour into a bowl.
Make a well in the center and add egg yolks, egg and salt.
With hands, mix egg into flour.
Add water 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
(Add only enough water to form dough into a ball.)
Turn dough onto well-floured cloth covered board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Cover.
Let rest 10 minutes. Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Roll dough, 1 part at a time, into paper thin rectangle, keeping remaining dough covered.
Roll rectangle around rolling pin; slip out rolling pin.
Cut dough crosswise into 1/8-inch strips for narrow noodles and 1/4-inch strips for wide.
Shake out strips and place on towel to dry, about 2 hours.
When dry, cook in 3 quarts boiling salted water about 12 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Serve with favorite spaghetti sauce.
Makes about 10 ounces (6 cups)

title: o henry bars
directions: Combine oats, Karo, brown sugar, vanilla and margarine; pat into a
13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°. Melt chocolate
chips and peanut butter together; spread over hot bars.

title: beets supreme
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar and water.
Boil 15 minutes.
Add beets.
Let stand 30 minutes or more.
Just before serving, bring to the boiling point.
Add 2 tablespoons butter.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: broccoli and orzo soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat the broth and carrot to boiling over high heat.
Stir in the pasta.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and pour over loaf; continue baking 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally with sauce.

title: missouri kraut
directions: Dice and fry bacon.
Add onion and saute.
Add kraut, tomatoes and sugar. Simmer about 1 hour. If lesser kraut flavor is desired cook faster and for a longer period of time.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Saute ground beef, onions and celery in oil until brown.
Mix in bean sprouts, beef bouillon and mushrooms.
Mix cornstarch with mushroom liquid until smooth and add to mixture.
Cook about 10 minutes, stirring constantly, and add soy sauce.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Take out 1 hour before placing in oven.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together and use for apples, strawberries, etc.

title: eat chocolate and lose weight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan with waxed paper. Whisk together cocoa, sugar and boiling water. Cool to lukewarm.

title: charlotte's turkey taco salad
directions: In microwave, crumble turkey; cook until no longer pink. Drain; mash turkey with potato masher to make into fine pieces. Add all other ingredients.
Serve on lettuce with grated cheese, black olives, sour cream and fresh tomatoes.
Serves 8.

title: haystack cookies
directions: Melt morsels until smooth.
Add nuts and noodles.
Mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix flour and baking powder by sifting.
Beat eggs and sugar. Add flour, milk and nutmeg, reserving a little flour for rolling out.
Cut in any shape and fry in hot lard.

title: chocolate dream cookies
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
On high speed, combine the sugar, butter and 1/2 cup cocoa until smooth.
Beat in eggs and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla until well combined.
Stir in flour gradually.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350° on greased cookie sheet. Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place half of lettuce in deep salad bowl.
Top with celery, green peppers, onion and peas, in that order.
Cover with rest of lettuce.
Spread mayo on top and sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Mix well and serve.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease a casserole dish.
Alternate layers of thinly sliced raw potatoes, onions, pats of butter and a mixture of flour and milk.
Repeat layers as needed.
Add enough milk to barely cover potatoes.
Top with strips of American cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 400° oven.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine brown sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Add pumpkin, eggs, corn syrup and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce the heat to 350°.
Bake 25 more minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: amanda's onion soup
directions: Heat Broiler.
Melt 1/4 cup unsalted butter in 5 quart saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add 4 large white onions, halved and thinly sliced; stir to coat with butter.
Cover and cook 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 1 tsp. sugar, cook uncovered stirring onions until slightly golden, about 6 minutes.
Add 1 Tbsp. flour, cook 1 minute longer.
Stir in 3 cans condensed Beef Broth, 1 can of water and 1/4 cup red wine, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: oven-baked potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes lengthwise into quarters.
Place, skin side down, in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl; brush over potatoes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Cook in 350° oven approximately 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken salad supreme(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: In large bowl combine chicken, grapes, celery, oranges and almonds.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, ReaLime, salt and nutmeg; add to chicken mixture.
Mix well.
Chill to blend flavors.
Serve on lettuce, garnish with grapes and almonds if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Bring oil, sugar, vinegar, wate, salt and pepper to a boil. Let cool and pour over vegetables.
Let set for 24 hours.

title: molded cheese salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello.
Let cool and add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: mighty meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato sauce and cheese, in a bowl.
Mold in to a loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven and top with tomato sauce and grated cheese. Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Crumble cake on bottom of glass bowl.
Layer pudding and strawberries mixed with glaze to the top.
Spread Cool Whip on top and chill.
Makes a pretty dish with layers.

title: company eggs
directions: Grease glass rectangular baking pan.
Spread grated cheese on bottom of dish.
Dot with butter.
Mix cream with seasonings.
Pour half of cream over cheese.
Add eggs (lightly beaten).
Pour rest of cream on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix all together thoroughly. Chill dough. Can be kept for several days. Roll in balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Cook at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Combine chicken, water, celery, bay leaf and salt in a 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Simmer, covered, until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth, cool and dice.
Set aside. Strain broth.
Add milk.
Set aside.

title: kolacki dough
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the milk and yeast, until well blended.
Mix yeast and milk together until the yeast is dissolved.
Then add to the mix and knead until your hands come clean.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to use, divide dough into 7-inch balls.
Roll out on floured board.
Fill.
Roll up and bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until browned.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant into thin slices about 3/4 inch thick.
Soak overnight in kosher salt, lemon juice and cold water.
Remove from the marinade; rinse and dip in 1 cup of milk.
Then lightly coat with self-rising flour.
Deep fry pieces until golden brown.

title: butterscotch party cake
directions: Heat and stir butterscotch pieces with the water until pieces melt; cool.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in butterscotch mixture. Stir together flour, salt, soda and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating with electric mixer on low speed after each addition.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch layer cake pans.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes; cool.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a shallow container, stirring until well combined.
Add chicken; cover and marinate in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours, turning once.
Drain and discard marinade.
Transfer chicken to rack of a shallow roasting pan, coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.
Cut into 2 ounce slices.
Yields 14 servings at 1 slice each.
Calories:
Exchanges:
2 lean meat.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool and ice.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Beat together sugar and Crisco and eggs.
Add warm applesauce and baking soda.
Sift together flour and baking powder and cinnamon, cloves, allspice and nutmeg.
Add flour mixture last. Add 1/2 box raisins and 1 cup nuts.
Bake 1 hour in tube pan.

title: punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, frozen orange juice, frozen lemonade, sugar, and water and stir until frozen juices are thawed.
When ready to serve, pour in punch bowl and add chilled ginger ale, and chilled champagne.
The first mixture can be made ahead of time and stored in refrigerator.
The champagne can be omitted.
Can make an ice mold decorated with maraschino cherries.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool; add thawed berries and applesauce.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: cheese balls
directions: Put all ingredients except nuts into large bowl.
Let stand at room temperature for 4 to 5 hours.
After cheeses are very soft and warm, mix very well by hand.
Make balls size of baseballs and roll in nuts.
Roll tightly in foil and close well.
Can be frozen for 6 weeks or stored in refrigerator.
Makes 10 to 12 balls.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before serving.

title: john's chicken cutlets
directions: Combine eggs with 1/2 cup of water; mix well.
Dip chicken in egg wash, then in flour to coat.
Dip in egg again and then dip in breadcrumbs to coat.
Fry until just browned in butter (about 5 minutes total).
Take 2 envelopes of Lipton Recipe Secrets golden herb with lemon and add 2 cups of water.
Mix well.

title: bread pudding
directions: Bake biscuits and set aside.
Beat eggs in a bowl.
Add in rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Break biscuits into liquid mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until brown.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Heat margarine in a 5-gallon pot. Add onion and celery; saut until lightly browned (about 5 minutes). Stir in paprika; add chicken, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Stir in water and chicken base. Cover and simmer until heated through, about 30 minutes. Put in steam table pans, two 12 x 20 x 6 x 1 and one 12 x 9 x 6. Add sour cream to each pan. Stir gently and put in oven at 250° until serving time. Ladle over parsley noodles. Do not overcook. Meat will become stringy. Makes 250 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Place in buttered casserole.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers, then add melted margarine.
Pour over crackers as evenly as possible.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mrs. croshaw's sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and put into oblong baking dish.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, water and salt in saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil, cover tightly and boil 3 minutes. Remove cover and continue cooking until syrup takes on a rich caramel color (320°).
Have peanuts spread out on a buttered shallow pan.
Pour caramel syrup over the peanuts and let cool thoroughly before breaking in pieces.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken; remove skin and bones.
Cut into small pieces. Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix soup and broth; bring to a boil.
Mix margarine, salt, pepper, flour and buttermilk; stir to form batter.
Pour over chicken the soup and broth.
Spoon batter over top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jon mazetti
directions: Brown green pepper and onions in shortening.
Add hamburger and cook until it loses its red color.
Cook noodles.
Add tomatoes to hamburger with Worcestershire sauce, pepper and salt. Layer noodles, hamburger and cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: jason's french toast
directions: Preheat skillet to medium-high heat.
Use 1/8 cup of Canola cooking oil.
Mix all ingredients.
Add spice last to prevent it settling to the bottom of the liquid.
Dip the bread, one slice at a time, into the bowl of liquid mix.
Turn to make sure each slice is coated well.
Cook until golden brown on each side.
Stack on a plate.
Sift on powdered sugar.
Top with your favorite lite syrup.

title: quick and easy dip for fruit
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend until smooth with an electric mixer.

title: hush puppies
directions: Chop onions and peppers.
Combine dry ingredients in a bowl. Add beaten egg, buttermilk, onions and peppers.
Deep fry by the spoonful.
Cook until golden brown.

title: cheddar-almond-broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
If using fresh broccoli, wash and cut into spears.
In a large saucepan, bring 1 inch of water to a boil.
Add the broccoli and salt.
Cook, covered, for 8 to 12 minutes or until crisp-tender.
(Or, cook the frozen broccoli according to the package directions.)
Drain the broccoli and transfer to a 2-quart rectangular or oval baking dish.

title: cheesecake ala george
directions: Measure 1 1/2 cups graham cracker crumbs; mix with 1/8 pound butter or margarine.
Press firmly into spring-form pan on bottom and up sides a bit.
Place in refrigerator to set while mixing cake.

title: caramel filling
directions: Combine in top of double boiler (or in microwave oven) caramels and milk.
Heat until caramels melt, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine, sugar and pecans.

title: matthew's favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well. Add combined flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well. Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts; mix well. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: low-fat soft tacos
directions: Brown meat, then rinse in a colander under hot water.
Let drain.
Return meat to pan, add taco mix and follow instructions on mix package to prepare taco meat.
Steam tortillas, and assemble tacos.
Makes about 6 to 8 tacos.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Mix the soup, milk, flour, mustard and pepper in a 3-quart saucepan until blended.
Stir over medium-high heat until almost boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese; stir until melted. Stir in egg yolks and broccoli until blended.
Cool slightly. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into broccoli mixture.
Pour into prepared dish.
Bake for 50 minutes, until top is golden and puffy and a knife inserted comes out clean. Makes 8 servings.

title: herbed fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt, thyme, marjoram, celery salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Add a few pieces of chicken to coat at a time. Heat shortening in skillet.
Fry chicken for 30 to 40 minutes without turning or lowering heat.
Turn once for even browning.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone and remove skin.
Shred breast meat and put back in the water.
Bring to boil.
Add carrots, celery and bouillon cubes, stirring for 5 minutes.
Add noodles.
Let boil until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: georgia pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients (except pecans). Stir until well mixed.
Spread pecan halves on bottom of pie crust and cover with filling.
Place pie in oven and immediately reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until mixture is firm in center.
Let cool before serving.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix together flour, sugar, powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening. Stir in orange juice, egg and peel, mixing just to moisten.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Spoon into pan.
Bake 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on rack for 15 minutes. Remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: roasted quartered potatoes
directions: In large roasting pan, toss together well, tossing occasionally for 1 hour, then toss in parsley.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake for 20 minutes, stirring halfway through until golden brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sugar free blueberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Pour contents in a 9-inch double dish pie shell.
Cook at 425 for 35 - 45 minutes.

title: chocolate raspberry cheesecake(diabetic recipe)
directions: Pour milk into blender container.
Add cottage cheese and fruit spread.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Add pudding mix. Cover; blend until smooth.
Pour pudding mixture into large bowl; gently stir in whipped topping.
Pour into 8-inch pie plate; smooth top.
Sprinkle with chocolate.
Freeze until firm, 6 hours or overnight.
Remove cheesecake from freezer about 15 minutes before serving.
Let stand at room temperature to soften slightly. Serves 8.

title: frozen daiquiris
directions: Blend well and store in freezer.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: curried fruit
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and curry powder. Bring to a boil. Drain fruit; arrange in 2-quart baking dish. Pour hot sauce over fruit. Garnish with cherries. Bake at 325° until it bubbles, 30 to 40 minutes. Serve hot.

title: caponata di melanzane(eggplant and bell pepper stew)
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan.
Add the onion and garlic. Saute until translucent.
Add the peppers and eggplant.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, season with salt, pepper and oregano; cook until eggplant and peppers are tender, but not mushy.

title: apple stuffing for your turkey
directions: Cook onions and celery in margarine for 5 minutes or until tender.
Combine with all other dried ingredients.
Add broth and toss lightly.
Yields stuffing for 10 to 12-pound turkey or 12 servings with approximately 130 calories per serving.

title: best ever sweet potatoes
directions: Precook sweet potatoes in boiling water until done.
Arrange in baking dish and pour over all other ingredients which have been mixed together.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate sheet cake icing
directions: Mix butter, cocoa and milk in saucepan. Heat over low heat, but do not boil. Remove from heat and add confectioners sugar, chopped pecans and vanilla.
Mix well.
Frost chocolate sheet cake as soon as removed from oven.
Cut cake in squares to serve. Makes 24 servings or 48 party size squares.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add other ingredients mixing well (do not use mixer).
Roll in balls the size of a walnut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten each with a glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
10 dozen.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix together; form into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts. Refrigerate at least 6 hours.

title: waldorf toss
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water. Combine cold water and ice to make 2 1/2 cups.
Add gelatin, stirring until thick.
Remove unmelted ice.
Combine fruit, celery and nuts.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: creamy lasagne
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and milk in saucepan; stir over low heat until smooth.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, dry dressing mix and scallions together well.
Spread a thin layer of cheese mixture on tortillas. Sprinkle green chilies, pimentos and black olives over tortillas lightly.
(Drain chilies, pimentos and olives well.)
Roll up and slice.

title: basic bavarian dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with sugar and boiling water.
Add cold water. Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir Cool Whip into Jell-O until blended.

title: pavlova
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In glass bowl, beat egg whites at high speed for 2 minutes.
Slowly add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time. Sprinkle cornstarch over egg whites; fold in.
Fold in vanilla and white vinegar.
Place egg white mixture in center of 12-inch baking plate.
Make a round shape, like a cake, indented in center.
Put plate in hot oven; reduce temperature to 250°.
Bake 1 hour 15 minutes, then turn off the oven and leave meringue inside 3 to 4 hours.
Should have crisp outer shell and center like marshmallow.
Add fresh fruit to creamy topping.
Spoon on top of cooled meringue.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Combine olive oil, onion, green pepper, scallions and tomato in large pot.
Cook until brown (approximately 5 minutes).
Add beans and tomato sauce.
Add spices to taste.
Cover and bring to boil. Turn down heat and simmer for 2 hours.

title: the best ever lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, rind, beaten egg yolks, salt and butter thoroughly.
Heat milk and water and pour over mixture.
Cook in heavy double boiler until thick.
Add lemon juice and stir.
Pour into baked pie shell.
When cooled, top with meringue.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Cook all together in saucepan until it thickens. Remove form heat, let cool a while. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: partridge pie
directions: Boil partridge in salted water until tender.
Allow to cool. Remove meat from bones and dice.
Save broth.
Saute onions in butter.
Add flour; stir.
Add broth and cook until thick.
Put pie crust in deep pie pan.
Add meat; pour filling over and cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add margarine; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press remaining mixture in pan.
Bake for 10 minutes; cool.
Top with nuts and whole chocolate pieces.

title: hot rolls
directions: Scald milk and add sugar and shortening.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Cool milk mixture and add to yeast mixture.
Add flour depending on the way it mixes; should look as stiff as biscuit dough when ready to cut.
Let rise 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: stuffed clams
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Could use this filling to stuff mushrooms too!

title: chinese vegetable soup
directions: Blanch tomato, skin and dice.
Saute in 3 tablespoons oil. Add with other vegetables to boiling broth.
Add seasonings after allowing vegetables to cook until tender.
Continue cooking 3 to 4 minutes.

title: hot beef sandwiches
directions: Rub spencer roll with pepper and oregano.
Put in pan with a little water.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour (no cover).
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice thin.
Cover meat with beer, bourbon and soup. Bake at 325° for 4 hours.

title: peach apricot preserves
directions: Combine fruit and sugar. Cook 20 minutes. Remove from heat and add jello.
Stir well. Place in jars and seal. Can be sealed with wax.

title: tuna shortcakes
directions: Melt cheese and milk together in microwave.
When sauce is smooth, add tuna.
Pour over individual servings of cornbread.

title: white chili
directions: Saute onion in oil in large kettle until tender.

Add garlic, chilies, cumin, oregano and cayenne pepper. Saute for 2 minutes, stirring frequently. Add beans and chicken stock. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Add chicken, 1 cup cheese, salt and black pepper to taste. Simmer until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally. Ladle into soup bowls.
Top with remaining cheese and sour cream, if desired. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Add stick of butter to elbow macaroni.
Cook until butter has melted.
Stir until macaroni is coated in butter.

title: big bertha
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, brown hamburger with 1 teaspoon chilies.
In separate container, simmer butter, onion (use according to taste), balance of chilies, tomatoes and seasoning for 30 minutes.
In buttered casserole dish, place a layer of Doritos chips, layer of hamburg, layer of liquid mixture, then layer of grated cheese.
Continue until chips, hamburg, liquid and grated cheese are all used.
Top with sour cream and bake until bubbles.

title: flitters
directions: Mix into a bowl, buttermilk, soda, salt and baking powder. Stir until batter is smooth.
Add flour and stir until batter is of a pancake batter consistency.
Melt shortening in a pan and cook as you would pancakes, at a medium temperature.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Prepare chicken breasts by rinsing and removing visible fat. Place one at a time in plastic bag or between sheets of waxed paper.
Using a kitchen mallet or a small frypan pound chicken to 1/2 inch thickness.
Place chicken in large bowl and cover with milk.
Cover and refrigerate from 1/2 to several hours.

Dredge chicken through bread crumbs and brown in 1 to 2 tablespoons olive oil in large frypan over medium heat (about 5 minutes each side). Place tomato sauce in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish and sprinkle with 1 to 2 teaspoons of Italian seasoning; stir gently. Carefully place chicken on top of sauce.
Slice a mushroom and place on top of each breast.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese on top. Bake for 25 minutes in 375° oven.
Serve over hot spaghetti or linguine.
Serves 4.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Bring fruit to a boil (just add 1/2 cup water).
Add all ingredients together.
Bake in preheated oven at 345° until begins to brown around edges, sprinkle pecans over top.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Grease baking dish with butter.
Pour mixture into dish.
Add enough milk to cover mixture.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 375° until thick.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all together except oats in pan and bring to a full boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oats.

title: summer pizza
directions: Flatten crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix softened cream cheese, mayo and Ranch dressing and spread on crescent crust.

title: jello mold with pretzel crust
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
In an electric mixer, beat Cool Whip, cream cheese and 10x sugar.
Spread mixture on cooled pretzel crust.
Dissolve Jell-O in water; add strawberries. Put in refrigerator; stir frequently until it starts to jel but not set (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Pour over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate overnight.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, cheese, pepper, basil, celery seed, onion powder, oregano, paprika and salt in bowl.
Dip chicken in evaporated milk and then coat with crumb mixture.
Place in lightly greased shallow roasting pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Brush with oil and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: eggnog bread
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and nutmeg in large mixing bowl.
Combine eggs, eggnog and oil.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir in raisins and apricots.
Pour into two greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
(Cover with foil after 40 minutes if bread browns too quickly.)
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on rack.
Wrap and store in refrigerator.

title: spareribs
directions: Combine mustard, chopped onion, brown sugar, apricots, chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce, liquid hot pepper and vinegar in blender.
Blend well.
Boil ribs for 1 hour.
Drain and cut into serving pieces.
Combine lemon juice and water in equal proportions sufficient to cover the ribs.
Marinate 4 hours or overnight. Brown ribs over charcoal, basting with sauce.
Freeze leftover sauce.

title: graham nut crust
directions: Combine ingredients.
Reserve 3 tablespoons.
Press remainder on bottom and up 2 1/2-inches on sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Crumble the cheese and mix well with all ingredients.
Flavor improves when this stands a few hours.

title: sunday morning pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Add eggs and whip lightly with electric mixer on medium speed.
Blend in milk and cream, a little at a time on medium speed.
Do not over mix, mixture should be smooth.

title: cookie bar
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and pat into bottom of a 9x13 pan.
Sprinkle the remaining ingredients over graham cracker crust, in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool, cut in small squares.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and butter. Heat about 3 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Quickly add oats, peanut butter and vanilla. Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper. Cool well.

title: pumpkin juice(halloween punch)
directions: Mix the Kool aid according to directions on the package.
You are looking for a pumpkin orange so you may need to add a drop of red food coloring to get the desired color.
Place in clean plastic gallon milk jugs and put into the freezer.
Take out and shake every once in a while.
Freeze until a light slush stage.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Sift flour with baking powder.
Add salt and milk and stir. Drop by teaspoon on top of stew, dropping spoon into broth each time to prevent sticking in batter.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Pour in pan and cool.

title: jiggers
directions: Prepare hamburger into 1/4 pound patties with half clove minced garlic in patties.
Arrange a hamburger on bottom of a large piece of foil.
Add 1 potato, 1 1/2 carrots and 1 small onion on top of pattie.
Top with 1/2 tablespoon of butter, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Fold up foil securely.
Place on cookie sheet.

title: virginia corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs into corn.
Combine sugar, flour, salt and pepper; add milk slowly until smooth.
Add to corn and egg mixture.
Last, pour in butter.
Put in 1-quart casserole and bake about 1 hour at 400°.
Check doneness by inserting knife; if it comes out clean, it's done!
Serves 4 to 6.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Combine ground round, eggs, oats, soup mix and remaining catsup.
Shape into a loaf.
Place in crock-pot.
Top with remaining catsup.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours or high 4 to 6 hours.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff; put aside.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time, to creamed mixture.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate with margarine.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1/2 cup sweetened condensed milk, eggs, biscuit mix and vanilla.
Spread evenly into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In medium bowl, combine remaining sweetened milk and coconut.
Spoon in small amounts evenly over chocolate mix.
Sprinkle nuts over top; press down.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool thoroughly; cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: cherry cream cheese tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place a paper cupcake liner in each cup of the muffin pan. Beat cream cheese with an electric mixer until fluffy. Add sugar and vanilla, beating well. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Lay a vanilla wafer flat side down in each muffin cup. Spoon cream cheese mixture over wafers. Bake for 20 minutes. Allow tarts to cool completely. Serve with pie filling on top.

title: my big bread pudding
directions: Reconstitute milk with water.
Pour milk over bread. Mix in raisins.
Beat eggs and add to bread mixture.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and pinch of salt.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg according to taste. Extra sugar may be needed depending on how sweet raisins are. Mix well.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Chop beef (1 package at a time) in blender; set aside.
Add 1 package of beef to cream cheese; add mustard, Worcestershire sauce, onion and mayonnaise.
Mix completely.
Shape cheese mixture into a ball on cheese tray; cover ball completely with second package of beef.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil 8 to 10 minutes.
Add oats and peanut butter.
Mix up and spoon onto wax paper.
Let it harden.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Add bananas.
Mix in flour and baking soda.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: ice cream
directions: For a special dessert or party refreshment, fill paper cups with scoops of ice cream.
Plant a lollipop for a flower with green gumdrops on a toothpick for leaves.

title: no peekie stew
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 3-quart casserole, combine stew meat, mushroom or chicken soup, onion soup mix and water.
Mix well. Cover; bake for 3 hours.

title: chocolate cookies with peanut butter chips
directions: Cream margarine and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually mix in with sugar mixture until a soft dough forms.
Add chips and drop by rounded spoonfuls onto baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked flounder
directions: Arrange fillets in
greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add onions and pour on lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a well-greased and mealed 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter well.
Add in powdered sugar and set aside for 7 minutes.
Add Cool Whip to cream cheese mixture; fold in pudding.
Crush Oreos in blender.
Alternately layer Oreo crumbs and pudding mixture in "flower pot" or "planter" (use white foam coffee cups), ending with Oreo crumbs on top.
Put in refrigerator.
Add silk flowers or plant "gummy worms" as garnish when it is time to serve.
Makes 10 to 12 desserts.

title: nanny's old-fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Add chocolate, cut in pieces, to milk in double boiler and heat.
(Or melt in microwave.)
When melted, beat with electric mixer until blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add to chocolate. Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour small amount over eggs, stirring vigorously. Return to double boiler and stir until thickens again.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Put into cooked pie shell or 8 tart shells and cover with meringue or whipped cream.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Place margarine in skillet, add minced onion, sugar, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook until margarine is melted, then add ground beef (cook until meat is brown).
Add tomato sauce and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Cook spaghetti.
Combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Place spaghetti in greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with cream cheese mix; then add meat mix.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: parfait de chocolate
directions: Using an electric mixer, beat the butter with sugar.
Add the 6 egg yolks and beat well.
Beat in the chocolate, liqueur and chopped nuts.
In another bowl, carefully beat the egg whites. Fold the chocolate cream into beaten egg whites.
Pour into an 8-inch tart pan with removable bottom.
Cover and freeze.
Half an hour before serving, move to the refrigerator.
Garnish with nuts, fruits or whipped cream.

title: hot "philly" spread
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all of the listed ingredients.
Pour into baking dish. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Take from oven and crumble Ritz or Town House crackers on top of casserole.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix and stir until it forms a ball. Add 1 1/2 cups of peanut butter. Mix well and then beat for 2 minutes. Pour into a greased pan. Cook over medium heat until done.

title: mamaw's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder and soda; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Combine wet and dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Place golf ball size portions of dough 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until edges are light brown.

title: hard cinnamon candy
directions: Place sugar, corn syrup and cold water into medium saucepan. Bring to slow boil and cook to hard ball stage (350°).
Turn off; beat and add 10 drops of cinnamon oil and food coloring.
Stir and pour onto cookie sheet dusted with cornstarch.
When cool, break into chips.

title: old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, milk and coconut.
Melt butter in ovenproof glass pie plate.
Pour mixture into melted butter in plate and bake in moderate oven (350°) until firm.

title: delish steak
directions: Mix together flour and salt. Rub 3 tablespoons flour into steaks.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Add steaks and brown on both sides.
Put into a medium size baking dish. Add onions and brown lightly. Spoon over meat.
Melt remaining butter.
Add mushrooms and brown, stirring in remaining flour, bouillon and cream. Simmer until slightly thickened.
Add olives.
Spoon over meat.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: apple walnut stuffing
directions: In large skillet cook celery and onion in butter until tender. Add water and bouillon.
Cook until dissolved.
In large bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Add celery mixture.
Mix well. Loosely stuff turkey just before roasting.
Place remaining stuffing in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until hot.

title: beef stew delight
directions: Mix soups in casserole dish and add meat. Cook in 325° oven for 3 hours, covered.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup with milk.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange in alternate layers, potatoes, onions and sauce.
Dot top with butter and cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, covered.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes or until tender.
You can use different cheeses.
Grate and layer with cheese.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Combine and mix sugar with evaporated milk and cinnamon.
Boil until soft ball stage.
Then add vanilla and nuts.
Stir up and pour on waxed paper; break into pieces.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Mash ingredients and mix well.
Makes 3 to 4 sandwiches. Add more pickle to juice to make tasty chip dip.

title: green bean variation
directions: Saute onion and
bell pepper in oil or drippings.
Pour half liquid off	beans.	Place
remainder
into	the saucepan. Add onion and bell
pepper
and
simmer until flavors are well blended, about 10 to 15 minutes, simmering over low heat.

title: leona's zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add oil.
Mix in flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt.
Fold in nuts, vanilla and squash. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: toasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Wipe off pumpkin seeds.
Do not wash.
In a bowl, combine 2 cups seeds, melted butter and 1/2 to 1 teaspoon salt.
You may also add Worcestershire sauce.
Put seeds in mixture until all coated. Spread on cookie sheets and bake at 250° for approximately 2 hours, stirring occasionally or until seeds are golden brown.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and eggs.
Add flour and meal.
Gradually add milk, margarine, lemon juice and rind.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bud's shepherd pie
directions: Brown hamburger in large skillet. Add lots of garlic salt. Add bouillon cubes to 1 1/4 cups hot water and dissolve. Pour in with browned hamburger. Thicken gravy with flour or cornstarch. Use Gravy Master to color. Add 2 cans of Green Giant whole kernel corn (drained). Simmer.

title: assorted fruit buffet
directions: In small mixing bowl, mix cream cheese, preserves and milk with an electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Spoon into the center bowl of a serving center.
Arrange desired fresh fruits around the mixture.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Serve fruit with cocktail picks.
Makes 12 cups of fresh fruit pieces and 1 2/3 cups of dip.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Stir until slightly thickened.
Gently spoon over fruit. Chill until firm, 3 hours.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour mix on top of margarine.
Do Not Stir.
Add 3 or more cups of sliced fruit.
Do Not Stir.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and some cinnamon on top.
Do Not Stir.
Bake at 425 for about 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple and juice in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread can of cherry pie filling over this.
Crumble cake mix over pie filling. Slice margarine and distribute evenly over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: simple salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix the broccoli, cauliflower and onion.
Add bacon.

title: russian tea(friendship tea)
directions: Mix together in Tupperware and cover.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup and hot water.

title: chocolate peanut butter candy
directions: In a large bowl mix well powdered sugar, oleo, Eagle Brand and peanut butter.
After mixing together all ingredients store in fridge overnight.
Shape into small balls and store in fridge until ready to dip into chocolate mixture.

title: grandma's mix
directions: Mix the above ingredients.
Eat & enjoy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In bowl mix egg, mayonnaise, cream of mushroom soup and onions. Add broccoli to mixture in casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese and Cheez-Its crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with Waverly crackers.

title: seafood casserole
directions: I usually make with one pound of imitation crab and no shrimp.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bones.
Save broth.
Cook rice in broth according to directions on box.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain and combine first 5 ingredients.
Add diced vegetables. Combine sugar, oil and vinegar; pour over vegetable mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Stir well before serving.

title: oyster sauce ribs
directions: In a saucepan, boil enough water to cover ribs.
Place ribs in boiling water and simmer with crushed or ground ginger for 45 minutes.
Using a colander, drain ribs well.
Combine and mix last 5 ingredients.
Add ribs to marinade and soak for 2-3 hours.
Broil or charcoal grill.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla. Add coconut and pecans.
Add egg whites.
Pour into three 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: venison vegetable stew
directions: In Dutch oven cook bacon; crumble and set aside.
Cook venison and onions in drippings until brown.
Add 3 cups water, tomato sauce, soup mix, bay leaf and Italian dressing.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook 1 1/2 hours or until meat is almost done.
Add carrots, celery and potatoes.
Return and cook 45 minutes to 1 hour until vegetables are done.
Combine flour and 1/2 cups water; stir and cook until thickened.
Remove bay leaf.
Add bacon.
Also good with moose meat.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Fill a 9-inch unbaked pie shell with cut up pieces of rhubarb. Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar.
Mix milk, eggs and 1/4 cup sugar.
Pour over rhubarb and sprinkle with flour.
Bake at 375° until an inserted knife comes out clean.

title: beef tip and noodles or rice
directions: Dredge beef in flour; brown in hot oil in a large Dutch oven, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients except noodles or rice.
Cover and bring
to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until meat	is tender.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: seven layer cookie
directions: Layer graham cracker crumbs, chocolate chips, coconut, butterscotch chips, Eagle Brand milk and chopped nuts in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: white house pink fruit punch(serves 12 to 16)
directions: Add all the ingredients, reserving ice until just before serving.
Add sherbet or garnishes as desired.

title: chocolate pistachio biscotti
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg and orange juice.
Sift in flour together with cocoa, baking soda and salt. Fold in nuts.
Divide batter in half and spread 1/2 batter on Pam-sprayed 11 x 4-inch cookie sheet or 12-inch oval.
Repeat with other half.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar; add eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and red coloring in a small bowl; add to creamed mixture. Sift together flour and salt; add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Dissolve baking soda in vinegar in a small bowl; add this with the vanilla to the red mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° in 2 (8-inch) rounds or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pans.

title: brownies
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over cake mixture; swirl with knife.
Bake at 350° per cake instructions.

title: punch
directions: Pour over ice cubes.
Float orange slices on top.

title: party mix
directions: *I use one 16 ounce box Wheat Chex, 6 cups Cheerios, 2 boxes sesame chips, 2 bags fish pretzels, 1 bag plain fish and 7 ounces shoestring potatoes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Cook spinach until tender, drain and place in refrigerator to chill.
Mix the mayonnaise, onion, horseradish and egg.
Combine with chilled spinach.

title: thumbprint cookies frosting
directions: Mix together butter, cream and brown sugar in pan.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Stir in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Frost Thumbprint cookies with warm frosting and dip in nuts.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar thoroughly; add cream cheese; next add 1 cup flour and 2 eggs and mix well. Then add 2 more eggs and 1 cup flour; mix well. Add the last 2 eggs and 1 cup flour; mix well. Add flavorings and pour into tube pan. Place in cold oven and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: low-fat pineapple angel food cake
directions: Mix together and put into Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Turn oven down to 325° for 20 minutes. Turn upside down and let cool.

title: new england stew
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Cook onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic over low heat, stirring often for about 8 minutes or until vegetables are soft. Add carrots, zucchini and yellow squash to skillet and stir over low heat for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add creamed corn, whole kernel corn (with liquid), corn muffin mix and eggs.
Pour in a large casserole.
Dot top with sour cream and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: taco sauce
directions: Chop stewed tomatoes and combine all ingredients until well blended. Place in an airtight container. Refrigerate sauce up to 7 days. Serving: 1 cup.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Mix cornbread mix, milk, eggs and corn together.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Pour 1/2 cornbread mixture in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Layer hamburger and onion, then jalapenos and cheese. Cover with remaining cornbread mixture.
Cook at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ham deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half, remove and mash yolks.
Stir in ham, mayonnaise, onion, mustard, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Spoon yolk mixture into egg white cavities.
Top each with pickle slice. Makes 12 appetizers or 6 salad servings.

title: seafoam icing
directions: Combine in a heavy sauce pan the sugar, water, corn syrup and salt.
Boil slowly without stirring until mixture will spin a long thread when a drop is dropped from a spoon.
Hold spoon high above the pan.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix meat, 1/2 cup soup, onions, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Press in bottom of pan firmly.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove and drain off fat.
Spread mashed potatoes on meat and top with remaining soup and cheese.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: prize winning poppy seed bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar; beat for 2 minutes.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture, alternating with milk (beginning and ending with dry ingredients).
Stir in extract and poppy seed.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Pour glaze over bread.

title: mary fann's cookies
directions: Cream sugars and
margarine;
add
eggs,
soda,
baking powder, salt and vanilla;
mix well.
Add flour, oats and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts as desired. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes
or until light brown.
If cookie is not firm enough, add more flour.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Heat vinegar, water, salt and butter and stir to boiling. Beat next 4 ingredients together and add to boiling mixture.
Cook until it thickens about 1 minute.
Set aside to cool.
(I usually double this recipe.)

title: killer brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Mix 2 cups of sugar and 3 eggs with a whisk.
Add to butter and chocolate mixture and whisk.
Add in flour, walnuts and vanilla.
Save 1 cup of this batter out.
Spread rest in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook egg noodles according to package directions. Rinse under cold water; drain and set aside.
Heat oven to 400°.

title: chicken mediterranean
directions: Cut chicken into 3 to 4 pieces.
Heat oil over medium heat and place meat in pan, turning after a few minutes.
Add vinegar, shallots, herbs and vegetables.
Cover and simmer for 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in butter and serve.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, mustard seed and celery seed. Pour over beans.
Cover and let stand several hours or overnight.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix water and margarine in 12 x 8-inch baking dish until margarine is melted. Stir in stuffing mix and 1/4 cup salsa. Arrange chicken over stuffing. Pour remaining 1/2 cup salsa over chicken. Cover dish with foil. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour until chicken is cooked thoroughly. Remove foil. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavored stuffing mix

title: meatball soup
directions: Combine eggs, bread crumbs, Romano cheese, parsley, onion, garlic and salt.
Add ground beef; mix well.
Form mixture into 48 balls.
In a skillet, brown meatballs, shaking pan often to keep balls rounded.
Drain off fat.

title: mock champagne punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large punch bowl.
Mix well. Serve immediately.

title: never-fail caramel frosting
directions: Mix butter, white and brown sugars and cream.
Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and vanilla.
Then add powdered sugar.

title: cheese ball
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients, except paprika, and mix thoroughly.
Spread wax paper heavily with paprika.
Roll cheese into a ball.
It will be soft.
Cover with paprika.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Place ball in refrigerator until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush the vanilla wafers and mix with fruit and nuts. Melt the marshmallows in canned cream and mix well into fruit nut mixture. Put mixture into loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Press well and store in refrigerator.

title: company salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Let cool.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Congeal.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook onions and celery in 2 or 3 cups water.
In large mixing bowl, combine cornbread, white bread, celery, onions, eggs, oleo, sugar, salt and pepper.
Moisten with chicken or turkey broth and the water the celery and onions were cooked in.
If you don't have enough broth, dissolve chicken bouillon cubes in hot water and use it or use canned chicken broth.
Add sage.
Make dressing mixture consistency of uncooked cornbread.
Pour into large greased shallow pan and bake approximately 45 minutes in 350° oven.
This amount will serve 25 to 30 people.

title: cream cheese glaze
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in remaining ingredients until smooth.
Spoon over bread.
Also good on Bundt cakes.

title: baked apples and onions
directions: Melt the butter in a baking dish.
Spread the first layer of onions on the bottom of the dish.
Arrange the apples on the onions.
Repeat the same sequence of layers.
Salt the layers as they are added and pour syrup over the top.
Cover the pan.
Bake at 350° until the ingredients are tender (about 20 minutes). Serves 6.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind cookies in the blender until they get to a soil like consistency.
Set aside.
Blend vanilla pudding and milk to pudding consistency.
Add cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip. Mix together.
Layer pudding mixture, then cookie mixture, starting with cookie mix and ending with cookie mixture.

title: busy day spanish rice beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix with Spanish rice in large bowl and add minced onions.
Put in 9 x 9-inch casserole dish and top with Cheddar cheese.
If you don't have time to grate cheese, just slice and put on top.
Cook at 425° in preheated oven until cheese is real bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Serve with barbecue, bread and pickles.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Beat together first 7 ingredients and pour in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over mixture.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, no longer.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Mix cornstarch and cheese.
Boil water.
Gradually add cheese, stirring over medium heat until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add spices.
Saute ham, then each vegetable separately in butter, adding each to soup.
Heat again, adding milk until desired thickness is reached.
Hearty enough for a whole meal!

title: chicken enchilada soup
directions: In large saucepan/stockpot place oil, chicken base, onions, and spices.
Saute until onions are soft and clear, about 5 minutes.
In a separate container add masa and 1 qt. of water. Stir until all lumps are dissolved.
Add to sauteed onions and bring to a boil.
Once the mixture starts to "bubble" continue cooking for approximately 2-3 minutes, stirring constantly.
This will eliminate the "raw" taste from the masa.

title: carrot salad
directions: Heat to a boil the tomato soup, oil, vinegar, sugar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour heated ingredients over carrots, onions and pepper strips.
Stir well and allow to marinate a couple of hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil the ingredients for one minute.
Pour over 3 cups rolled oats.
Add 1/2 cup nuts and/or 1/2 cup coconut.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.
Makes about 3 to 4 dozen.
Cookies will get firm in about 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: working woman's lasagne
directions: Saute ground round and garlic in oil.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano; simmer 5 minutes.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking soda.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
DO NOT BEAT.
Place in greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet syrup
directions: Mix and boil for at least 15 minutes or until thick.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, buttermilk, eggs, coconut, vanilla and a pinch of salt.
Mix together and pour into frozen pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: christmas nut caramels
directions: Cook in saucepan the corn syrup, condensed milk and sugar, stirring constantly, until it forms a firm ball when it is tested in cold water.
Add the butter, nuts and vanilla.
Do not beat. Pour into buttered pan.
Cut and wrap when set.

title: chicken normandy
directions: Blend flour, salt, oregano and pepper in plastic bag.
Coat chicken.
Set aside 1 tablespoon flour mixture.
In electric frypan, add olive oil and brown chicken.
Combine wine and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Add onion.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover.
Cook over low heat 45 minutes.
Cook mushrooms in butter.
Drain.
Remove chicken to Corning Ware platter.
Keep warm.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes and sugar to wine mixture.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add flour mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over chicken.

title: dutch pound cake
directions: Secret to success, have ingredients at room temperature and beat well.
Beat butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and milk gradually and beat well.
Add extract and beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and turn oven up to 400° (without removing cake) and bake 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Melt the margarine and allow to cool. In mixer, beat eggs and add sugar, flour, margarine and vanilla. Stir
in
chocolate
chips
and nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake
for 45 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool before serving.

title: robin's potato soup
directions: Melt butter in pan. Add onion, potatoes.
Cover with water mixture to just top of potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are done. Add milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook on low until cheese melts.
Serve warm.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Bring crushed pineapple with juice to a boil.
Stir in Jell-O to dissolve.
Cool.
Stir in the buttermilk and fold in the Cool Whip.

title: pickles
directions: Pour salt over the cucumbers, onions and bell peppers.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Drain; do not wash.
Pack in jars after drained.
Bring to a boil remaining ingredients.
Let boil 3 minutes.
Let cool and then pour in jars over cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Wait 3 weeks before eating.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet and bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Put berries in oblong type baking dish, approximately 6 x 11 inches, cover with pineapple.
Pour on dry cake mix and scatter nuts over top.
Melt butter and drizzle over all.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: red bean lasagna
directions: Cook onion, carrot and garlic in oil.
Add undrained tomatoes, beans, parsley, sugar, oregano, basil and salt.
Bring to boil. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add slightly mashed bean mixture with mushrooms and simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
Combine egg with half of the 3 cheeses.
Spread 1/2 cup bean mixture in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish.
Arrange two noodles atop.
Spread with 1/3 cheese mixture, then with 1/3 bean mixture.
Repeat layers twice. Bake covered in 375° oven 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pineapple, Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice. Pour into pie shells. Refrigerate. Makes 2 pies.

title: pork-curry pockets
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the sandwich spread and curry powder.
Stir in the finely chopped pork or chicken, carrot, coconut and green pepper.
Mix well.

title: nugget cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix until well blended.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After cooling, ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: hurry up breakfast coffee cake
directions: Sift flour,
sugar,
baking
powder
and salt together. Beat egg and
add
milk and shortening.
Stir liquids into dry ingredients, mixing only enough to dampen all the flour.
Pour into a greased
pan.
Sprinkle with crumb toppings and bake in hot oven at 425° for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 (9 x 9-inch) recipe.

title: homemade fudge mix
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt, flour and baking powder.
Cut into Crisco until like coarse cornmeal.
Set aside.
Beat eggs and vanilla.
Add 3 cups mix; stir.
Add nuts.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Sift confectioners sugar over top.
Cut; makes 16 squares.

title: creole shrimp sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill thoroughly.
Sprinkle grated egg yolk over top just before serving.

title: poor man's stew
directions: Drain all cans of vegetables.
Put all ingredients into a very large stew pot.
Cook on low heat until done. Add salt and pepper to your own taste.
Serves 6 to 8 people or more.

title: easy brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spray 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Equal out batter and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Thaw and drain strawberries.
Fold whipped cream into cream cheese. Add mayonnaise, strawberries, marshmallows, pineapple and pecans, stir and mix.
Place in 2 1/2-quart oiled mold (could use Pyrex dish) and freeze.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to boil for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter until melted.
Add corn flakes.
Turn out onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water (use water from potatoes).
Important to let water cool to lukewarm.
Mix with remaining ingredients to make a stiff dough.
Let rise until double in size; knead down. Bake at 400°.
Makes 4 dozen rolls.

title: onion cheese soup
directions: Brown onions in butter; blend in flour.
Stir in hot milk gradually.
Add salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Serve hot. Serves 4 to 6.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add chicken wings.
Marinate for 2 hours.
Roast, uncovered, with marinade, for 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes, at 350°.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cut carrots crosswise on the bias in 1-inch chunks.
Cook, covered, in salted, boiling water until just tender; drain. Combine next 4 ingredients in small saucepan.
Add orange juice; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles. Boil 1 minute.
Stir in butter, then pour over hot carrots, tossing to coat evenly.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in blender and blend for 6 seconds. Pour into greased pie plate. Sprinkle over batter the meat (cooked and drained), cheese and mushrooms. Punch down into batter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Makes its own crust.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and chopped onions.
Drain off fat. Add balance of ingredients and mix together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix together and put into a 13 x 9-inch pan or large casserole.
Cover with foil and place in refrigerator overnight. When ready to bake, remove foil.
Rub top with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake in two 9-inch pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan that is greased and floured at 300° for 1 hour.

title: taglianini
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain off liquid.
Add remaining ingredients, uncooked noodles.
Use 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese on top and return to oven for 15 minutes.
Can be frozen or prepared ahead and heated.

title: zucchini cheese casserole
directions: Mix zucchini, cheese, 3/4 cup bread crumbs and onion.
Stir in beaten egg and wine.
Put mixture in greased casserole.
Mix remaining bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: deep frying batter
directions: Mix all together.
(Good for onion rings, shrimp, etc.)

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese; add sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Pour into buttered pan.
Refrigerate before cutting into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend together all ingredients except broccoli.
Add all ingredients to drained broccoli.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Combine
first	five
ingredients
and	mold into ball. Roll in pecans.	It taste the best if made the day before.

title: fried fish
directions: Rinse fish and pat dry.
In shallow pan combine buttermilk, mustard and pepper.
Place bread crumbs on sheet of waxed paper. Dip fish in buttermilk mixture and coat with bread crumbs.
Lightly spray large skillet with Pam spray.
Cook fillets over medium high heat for four to five minutes on each side, or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine milk, flour and 1/2 cup sugar; mix well.
Pour batter in pan over butter; do not stir.
Combine remaining ingredients (1/2 cup sugar, fruit and cinnamon).
Pour into center of batter; do not stir.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Also can be baked on a jelly roll pan (large) for 15 to 20 minutes at 400° or until done.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and whip with a fork.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: nacho cheese
directions: Spray pan with Pam Release.
Mix last 4 ingredients with wire whip; add cheese.
Melt in double boiler.
