title: shrimp sauce for pasta
directions: Cook garlic in oil; add shrimp.
Cook a few minutes and remove from shrimp with slotted spoon.
Add tomatoes, chicken broth, tomato paste and herbs; cook until it measures around 2 cups. Just before serving, add seafood and serve over the pasta of your choice, cooked al dente.
This is an excellent pasta dish to use summer tomatoes.

title: easy chocolate nut clusters
directions: Mix chocolate and milk together.
Heat mixtures on top of stove or in a microwave until chips are melted and mixture can be thoroughly combined
Remove form heat and stir in nuts.
Drop teaspoonfuls on waxpaper and let set until firm.
Can be stored in a bowl, box, or tin, covered for up to 2 weeks at room temperature.

title: orange soy chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish and sprinkle with curry powder. Spoon thawed orange juice and soy sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes and serve with rice.
(For a special treat, cook rice with chicken broth, saffron, cardamon and white raisins.)

title: creamy orange salad
directions: Mix jello and cream cheese with water (mix with mixer). Refrigerate until slightly jelled.
Whip the whipping cream and add it and all other ingredients to first mixture.
Chill and serve.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: slow-cooked pork barbeque
directions: Rinse roast and place in slow cooker. Sprinkle with salt. Add 1 bottle of BBQ sauce and cola to slow cooker. Cover and cook on low for 6 hrs.

title: tahoe brunch(must be prepared 24 hours in advance)
directions: Butter the bread with the softened butter and set aside.
In a 10 to 12-inch skillet, melt the 1/2 cup butter and brown the mushrooms and onions over medium heat for 5 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Season to taste with salt and pepper; set aside.
Cook the sausage and cut into bite-sized pieces.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and flavoring.
Stir in ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise and line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook pudding as directed on box and pour over Twinkies.
Spread on fruit topping.
Cover with other half of Twinkies.
Top with Cool Whip.
Cool 1 hour and serve.
Keep remaining in refrigerator.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine sugar, water and butter in a saucepan.
Boil to soft ball stage; remove from heat.
Add pecans.
Beat until hard, then drop by spoonfuls onto paper.

title: summer shake
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend on high for about two minutes or until smooth.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix first four ingredients one at a time as listed; add nuts. Press in pan or shape into balls.
Chill 1 hour in freezer.
Dip in mixture of chocolate and paraffin that has been melted.
Use toothpicks; it makes it easy to dip balls in chocolate.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased serving or fondue dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in 6 to 8 cups water. Remove from cooker; pull or cut into bite size when cool. (Whole chicken, remove skin.) Bring broth and extra water, if needed, to boil. Cut soft tortilla shells into bite size and drop into rolling boil broth. Reduce heat; cover for about 10 minutes, then add chicken. Cook long enough to warm chicken.

title: easy mexican bean dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of pan. Heat chili and spread on top of cream cheese. Spread onion and jalapenos next. Add cheese. Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubble. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix syrup, sugar and nuts.
Cook over medium heat in iron skillet until honey colored.
Peanuts will begin to pop.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Return to heat and beat vigorously.
Pour onto greased (buttered) cookie sheet.
Cool and break.

title: pepper jelly
directions: In blender with 1/3 cup of water, pulverize peppers.
Combine peppers, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a hard boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 2 bottles Certo and a few drops of green food coloring.
Yields 12 to 13 half pints.

title: creamy mushroom soup
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Stir sliced mushrooms into soup.
Add some chopped fresh or dried parsley.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Add wine just before serving.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts in a 9 x 13-inch pan; pat smooth.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix instant chocolate pudding and milk until thick and creamy.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: make ahead salad
directions: Layer first 8 ingredients in above order.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and frost top of salad.
Top with cheese and seal with plastic wrap.
Chill at least 12 hours.
Toss before serving. Great with ham or turkey.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix white cake mix according to package directions except use 2 whole eggs instead of whites.
Arrange rhubarb in a well greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and Jell-O.
Top with marshmallows.
Cover with cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Put oleo in 1 cup water.
Add 1/2 cup water.
When cool, add yeast, sugar, salt and eggs.
Gradually add flour.
Let raise until double.
Punch down, make into rolls and let raise.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: aunt sue's fluffies
directions: Whip egg whites and cream of tartar.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Whip until batter peaks (add food coloring, if desired). Line cookie sheets with brown paper bags.
Bake at 275° for 40 minutes.

title: family breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken maria
directions: Melt butter with paprika and onion flakes.
Dip chicken in this mixture, then bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
While chicken cooks, cook the broccoli and drain it.
Drain the peaches (or pears can be used).
Arrange broccoli, chicken and peaches in a shallow pan.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream for sauce and pour over food in pan.
Broil for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: fish fry
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour and seasoning.
Set aside.	In a separate bowl blend beer and egg.
Beat until frothy.
Dip fish in wet ingredients and then dredge in dry.
Let sit for 10 minutes.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Serve with Hush Puppies.

title: maple glazed chicken wings
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Pour over wings and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
May be grilled or baked 1 hour at 350°.

title: pecan dreams
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix by hand to blend.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Place balls on lightly greased cookie sheet, pressing each ball with heel of your hand until balls are about 1/2-inch thick.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 20 minutes or until bottoms are golden brown.
Cool.
Makes 18 cookies.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Put pie crust in pan.
Add apples.
Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Chunk oleo on top.
Add top crust.
Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken wings
directions: Place chicken wings in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Make sauce by mixing remaining ingredients and pouring over chicken wings. Bake, covered, for 30 to 45 minutes, then remove cover and bake an additional 15 minutes, or until done.

title: ginger sprinkles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix oil and 3/4 cup sugar thoroughly. Add egg and beat well.
Stir in molasses.

title: peaches in cream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions (add 1 teaspoon of vanilla).
Cool cake and split each layer.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: chocolate-strawberry refresher
directions: In blender, combine yogurt, milk, chocolate syrup and strawberry syrup.
Cover and blend until smooth.
To serve, pour into tall glasses over ice cubes.
Makes 3 servings.

title: party pie
directions: Press pecans into bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Prick the sides only and bake shell.
Cool.

title: crock-pot hamburg stew
directions: Cut potatoes into small pieces.
In frying pan, brown hamburg and then drain off grease.
In crock-pot, add corn and tomato soup, right from can, onion and potatoes with 1/2 cup of water. Add hamburg.
Put crock-pot on low and leave on for 8 to 10 hours (while you are at work).
Serve with warm French bread.

title: turkey tomato soup
directions: Prepare soup as directed on can.
Drain and rinse pinto beans under running water.
Add pinto beans and cooked turkey to soup. Serve with your favorite crackers and green salad.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix all together and chill 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°, about 6 to 8 minutes. Frost when cooled. Mix butter and sugar, eggs and vanilla, then add other ingredients.

title: zucchini bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice onions and squash 1/8-inch thick and place in a large bowl.
Salt thoroughly; cover and allow to rest overnight. Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a rolling boil.
Add zucchini and onions to pickling solution.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pack pickles into hot sterilized pint jars.
Fill to 1/2-inch of top with pickling solution.
Seal. Makes 3 pints.

title: low country hot dip
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Saute onion, bell pepper and green onions in butter in a small frying pan over low heat until the vegetables are soft, but not brown, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to a large mixing bowl and add the Worcestershire, garlic salt and cream cheese and mix well.
Add the mayonnaise, pecans and dried beef and mix well.
Cut a slice off the top of the loaf of bread to serve as a lid.
Remove enough of the inside of the loaf to form a cavity large enough to hold the cream cheese mixture.
Pour the mixture into the cavity.
Replace the lid.
Wrap the loaf completely in aluminum foil and place it on a baking sheet.
Bake for 1 hour.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: millionaire's cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tangy meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine ketchup, sugar and mustard. Reserve 4 tablespoons for topping.

title: lemon fish roll-ups
directions: In small saucepan, melt 1/3 cup butter.
Add 1/3 cup lemon, 2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
In medium bowl, combine 1 1/3 cups rice, 1 cup cheese, 1 package broccoli and 1/4 cup lemon mixture.
Divide among 8 fillets; roll-up and place seam-side down in 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining sauce.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until fish flakes with fork.

title: chocolate chip and date cake
directions: Dice dates into bowl. Sprinkle soda over dates and pour boiling water over -- let cool. Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, vanilla, cocoa and flour. Beat together, then add date mixture. Pour into 13 x 10 cake pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over the batter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: one hour dinner rolls
directions: Mix 1/4 cup water and yeast.
In separate bowl, mix together 1 1/2 cups of water, sugar and salt. Add yeast mixture, then add 4 1/2 cups flour.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Knead down and shape. Brush with melted butter.
Let rise 15 minutes. Bake 15 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: karen's chewies
directions: Mix in order:
brown sugar, flour, 3 eggs, nuts, vanilla, and margarine.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream together butter or Crisco and sugar. Stir together baking powder, buttermilk, soda and salt.
Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 33 minutes. Frost with Caramel icing.

title: indian sun bread(modern)
directions: Combine yeast with 2 1/4 cups flour in bowl.
Heat water, shortening, sugar and salt.
Add to flour.
Beat until mixed. Add remaining flour and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in a large greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm spot until doubled in bulk.
Divide in half.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water; drain.
Combine in bowl soup, egg, cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Mix with broccoli.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with crackers over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: better than robert redford
directions: Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: one bowl chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in 1 1/2-quart bowl on High for 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted and smooth.
Stir in vanilla, salt and walnuts. Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into small squares.
Makes 2 dozen pieces.

title: plain cake
directions: Mix well and pour into a greased and floured sheet cake pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chuck wagon ranch beans
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and brown in frying pan.
Put bacon into a large crock-pot or Dutch oven and drain grease from frying pan.
In same frying pan, add hamburger and brown.
Add hamburger to the crock-pot and drain off grease from frying pan.
Saut onion in same pan, then add to crock-pot.
Add all the beans to the crock-pot and stir to blend.
In the same frying pan, add the brown sugar, ketchup, mustard and vinegar.
Heat until the sugar has dissolved.
Add to the crock-pot.
Heat the crock-pot until beans are hot.
Can be eaten right away or slow cooked for hours.

title: ruthie's beef in wine sauce
directions: Mix soup, soup mix, mushrooms and sherry.
Pour over cubes in large (2-quart) casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours or longer at lower temperature.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar and beat until smooth. Mix the flour in with the baking powder and beat until well blended.
Add lemon zest and heavy or sour cream and beat until smooth.
Add apples and mix gently with a spoon to coat well.

title: cornbread squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onions until tender.
Crumble cornbread and mix with drained squash and onions.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350°. As soon as taken out of oven, make holes with a straw and pour cream of coconut all over it.
Let cool, cover and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: pineapple mold
directions: Mold in 1 1/2-quart mold.

title: green chili stew
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown half of pork in oil.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until pork is tender. Serves 10.

title: kourabiedes(greek christmas cookies)
directions: Beat oleo or butter and Crisco.
Add baking powder, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Slowly add flour until the dough can be shaped and handled.
Shape into crescent shape and place on greased sheets. Place 1 whole clove in each cookie before baking.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cookies will be firm and very light brown. Remove from tray and roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Then store covered in powdered sugar.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add salt and pepper and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add green pepper and tomatoes.
Cook for an additional 10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread crushed pineapple on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Cut butter into small pats.
Place pats over entire cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over everything.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup margarine, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese; stir well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Crush cereal and stir in remaining butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Garnish with lemon and parsley (optional).

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut one thin lengthwise slice from each zucchini.
Cut small slice from each end.
Scoop contents out of each one and set aside. Cook meat and onions in oil.
Mix 1/4 cup tomato sauce with egg and bread crumbs and add to meat and onions.
Blend well and fill zucchini shells.
Place on a greased baking dish.
To the remaining tomato sauce add oregano, minced garlic, basil and salt and pepper to scooped out zucchini.
Pour this mixture over filled shell. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes at 350°, uncovered last 10 minutes.

title: becky's banana pudding
directions: In bowl, mix sugar, flour, egg yolks, milk and vanilla. Beat on high until mixed well. Pour into saucepan and cook until it begins to thicken. Let cool completely. Get your first layer of vanilla wafers and bananas ready. Pour into 1st layer and continue.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix vinegar and oil together.
Pour over peas and other ingredients.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Keep in tight covered dish.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pinch off and roll on floured board.
Fill with fruit and fry slowly.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour one-half of batter in pan, then add one-half of cheese and rest of batter.
Add remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minuets or until done.

title: peanut clusters
directions: *Do not use margarine, butter or oil.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Beat half and half with eggs and flour until smooth.
Split open chiles.
Rinse out seeds and drain on paper towels.
Mix cheeses and reserve.
Put chiles and egg mixture in deep 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour tomato sauce over top and sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until cooked in center.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Grease and flour cake pan.
Mix together.
Put most of the batter in the pan.
Add fresh berries.
Pour rest of batter over berries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: tetrazzini shawna
directions: Mix flour and oil in large pan over medium heat (roux).
Add milk, stirring so not to clump.
When mixture starts to thicken, whip in wine.
Add other ingredients except vermicelli.
Cook vermicelli in separate pot with water until al dente.
Combine pasta and mixture; bake 10 minutes.
Top with cheese and parsley. Serve.
Viva Italiano!!
Shawna!

title: clam dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and season to taste with anything, even cottage cheese.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and add eggs and milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 300°.

title: chocolate-peanut clusters
directions: Combine peanut butter, butterscotch morsels and chocolate chips in a saucepan over low heat.
Cook until melted.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Store in refrigerator in covered
container.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sherried creamed onions
directions: Peel onions, cut into thick slices.
Melt oleo; add onions and salt, cover and cook until tender.
(Approximately 20 minutes.)

title: brunswick stew
directions: Shred chicken in chunks.
Pour all other ingredients in a slow cooker or crock-pot.
Cook on low heat for 8 to 10 hours.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder together.
Add to cream mixture, alternating with milk.
Stir in vanilla extract and blend well.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Wrap in foil to keep.

title: fruit compote
directions: Combine all fruit.
Blend well.
Stir in pudding mix.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Serves 8.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and egg in bowl.
Add milk, vanilla and flour.
Grease pan.
Pour cake batter in pan.
Sprinkle blueberries on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked apple
directions: Core apples and peel a small crown of skin off the top. Sprinkle with a little cinnamon.
Turn apples upside down and pour soda into deep frypan.
Cover pan and cook on top of stove until done.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix fruit cocktail, pineapple and oranges.
Just before serving, add fresh fruit.
Serve as is or over ice cream or pound cake.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat.
Add and mix the remaining ingredients.
Toss all into crock-pot.
Cook on low approximately 8 hours.

title: bacon-cheese puffs
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg yolk and onion in large bowl.
Beat well until smooth and blended.
Stir in baking powder and bacon pieces.
(Mixture may be covered and stored in refrigerator until ready to use.)
Place crackers on paper plate and top each cracker with 1/2 teaspoon mound of cheese mixture.
For 6 crackers, heat in microwave for 30 seconds.
Serve hot.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal/milk and let it stand 15 minutes.
Add other ingredients and blend well.
Pour into well-greased skillet.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle with cheese on top.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Pour cake mix into bowl.
Make hole; add 1 egg, then another, until all 4 have been added.
Beat after each addition.
Add oil, 4 teaspoons lemon juice and rind; then add cooled jello.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit lizzies
directions: Chop all fruits and nuts.
Then combine with 1/2 cup flour to coat well.

title: chili-lime pork
directions: Use a large size (14 x 20-inch) oven bag.

title: apple fritters
directions: Combine egg, milk, melted butter, and brown sugar in mixing bowl.
Mix together using a fork.
Stir in the lemon rind, lemon juice, apples, and vanilla extract.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir the flour mixture into the batter, using a fork or spoon, being careful not to overmix.
Preheat oil (about an inch deep) in skillet to 350 degrees. Drop batter off the end of a tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry to a golden brown. Turn so they will brown evenly.
Remove from oil using a slotted spoon or tongs and place on paper towels.
Allow to cool.
Makes 25 to 30 fritters.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt margarine.
Do not use iron pot (crawfish will turn dark).
Add to pot onions, bell peppers and garlic.
Saute 5 minutes and add crawfish (shrimp), paprika, Cajun seasoning, pepper, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat until simmering.
Add water mixed with cornstarch.
Bring to a simmer and cook for 30 minutes on low heat.
Serve over rice.

title: no-fat apple cake
directions: In small bowl, mix apples, walnuts and cinnamon; put aside.

title: green cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes in a buttered and floured Bundt pan (or angel food pan) at 350°.

title: ambrosia fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and yogurt until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 2 cups or 8 servings; 4 tablespoons per serving.

title: old fashion caramel icing
directions: Boil 3 cups sugar and milk for 3 minutes.
In a skillet, melt 1 cup sugar over medium heat, stirring.
Add sugar and milk mixture, stirring quickly.
Add the oleo and vanilla.
Stir vigorously until of spreading consistency.
If mixture seems too thick, add a little milk.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and butter.
Add one egg at a time. Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk.
Pour batter in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.

title: dieter's coffee ice
directions: Combine sugar and coffee powder.
Add boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Freeze 2 hours or until firm.

title: cream soup mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield 3 cups mix.
Diabetic exchanges: 1/3 cup of mix equals 1 skim milk, 1 starch, also 149 calories, 168 mg sodium, 5 mg cholesterol, 25 mg carbohydrate, 10 gr protein, 1 gm fat.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese.
Mix all ingredients; chill overnight.
Roll into 1 or 2 balls.
Roll in crushed pecans.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with soda.
Combine margarine, the sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs and gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts (batter will be stiff).
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.
For chocolate chocolate chip cookies, substitute instant chocolate pudding.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Scald milk and pour over.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix in rest of stuff.
Use 9 inch round baking pan, greased.
Bake at 425 degrees for 40-45 minutes.

title: popovers
directions: Mix
ingredients well and pour into greased muffin pan. Fill each
only 1/2 full.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven. Centers
will be hollow.
Pop open and fill with butter or honey.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Mix flour, spices, soda and baking powder together.
Add eggs to creamy mixture alternately with flour mixture.
Mix well.
Gently add berries.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes in 3 layer pans, floured and greased. Cool.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in layers at 350° until cake turns loose from sides of pan (about 35 to 40 minutes).

title: ladyfingers
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In it, combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture reaches boiling point.
Cook to hard boil stage (250°) without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Meanwhile, beat egg whites to soft peaks.

Gradually add gelatin, beating to stiff peaks. Add vanilla and pour hot syrup slowly over egg white mixture, beating constantly on mixer at high speed until soft peaks form and mixture starts to loose its gloss.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Cook potatoes. Pare and slice thin.
Preheat oven to 350°. Arrange in baking dish a third of potatoes, salt, pepper and cheese.
Repeat twice using rest of ingredients.
Bake about 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: double chocolate fudge
directions: In saucepan, over low heat, melt semi-sweet chocolate chips with 2/3 cup condensed milk, 1 tablespoon milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Remove from heat; stir in 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread evenly into foil-lined 9-inch square pan.

title: chicken a la eansor
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with Swiss cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine; stir well. Spoon sauce over chicken and cheese.
Prepare stuffing according to package directions and place on top of soup layer.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: oreo angel cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions; fold in cookies.
Spoon into ungreased, 10-inch tube pan.
Bake according to directions.
Cool.

title: potato cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add potatoes, milk and eggs and mix thoroughly.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to potato mixture.
Bake in greased and floured angel food pan in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add milk, sugar and cocoa. Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 1/2 to 2 minutes and remove from stove. Add frosting mix and flavoring.
Beat until cool enough to put on cake.

title: brownie cake with icing
directions: Bring to boil oleo, oil, cocoa and water.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Mix with chocolate mixture. Add eggs and buttermilk.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Place all ingredients in large kettle and season to taste. Cook over slow heat for 2 weeks.
One medium size elephant will serve 762 people, but if extra guests should arrive, one rabbit may be added to "stretch" the stew.

title: hawaiian dip
directions: Cut center out of bread.
Set aside.
Drain juice out of spinach.
Mix spinach, onion soup mix and sour cream; pour in center of bread.
Use the bread that was in the center for dipping.

title: macaroni-cheese-beef casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner according to package; set aside.
Place ground beef in a skillet, stirring until it crumbles; drain.
Combine macaroni and cheese dinner, beef and tomatoes in a lightly greased baking dish.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Blend together cheese and margarine.
Add other ingredients in order.
Shape into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork.

title: fried rice omelette
directions: Wash and dice onion.
Rinse and cook ham and dice.
Scald green bean and diced carrot.
Remove and drain.
Saute diced onion with 1 tablespoon oil.
Add cooked rice to stir until tender.
Add green bean.
Cook ham and diced carrot to stir.
Add seasoning; stir-fry until done and remove.
Fry beaten egg with oil as omelette wrapping.
Put the fried rice on a side.
Wrap in semi-circle; fry and seal.
Serve.

title: stuffed pepper casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add all ingredients in iron skillet.
Cover with sliced cheese.
Place in oven until cheese melts.

title: chicken and potatoes with rosemary
directions: Peel and slice potatoes, 1/4-inch thick.
Microwave 8 minutes until tender.
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch strips.
Brown chicken and garlic in oil over medium-high for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and rosemary.
Saute until potatoes are lightly browned.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: sausage balls
directions: Note:
Let ingredients set until room temperature.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs and add to cheese. Stir in sugar, butter and flour. Bake at 375° for about an hour. Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg on top and bake.

title: south of the border pizza
directions: Coat two 12-inch pizza pans with nonstick cooking spray; sprinkle with cornmeal. Divide the bread dough in half; roll each portion into a 12-inch circle. Transfer to prepared pans. Build up edges slightly; prick dough thoroughly with a fork. Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Meanwhile, in a skillet, cook the beef, onion, yellow pepper and garlic over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in refried beans, salsa, chilies and chili powder; heat through. Spread over the crusts; sprinkle with cheese. Bake 6 to 7 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Top with tomatoes and lettuce; serve immediately.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll ball in 3/4 cup chopped fresh parsley.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Blend with a fork.
Press onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice. Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning. Spread bean dip on bottom, then avocado mix, then sour cream mixture, then tomatoes and top with cheese and scallions. Serve with chips alongside.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In mixing bowl beat eggs, cream, salt, pepper and nutmeg with whisk.
With a fork, prick sides and bottom of pie shell.
Make 2 or 3 layers of cheese and bacon bits in bottom on pie shell.
pour eggs and cream mixture over top of layers.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown and puffy.
Let cool a few minutes and slice into serving pieces. Serve with salad.
Refrigerate leftovers and reheat.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Drain juice from pork and beans.
Slice sausage into bite size bits and brown lightly.
Chop onion and brown lightly in sausage grease.
Mix barbecue sauce and brown sugar, then stir in sausage, onion and pork and beans.
Simmer on low 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash, cap and cut up strawberries.
Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until clear and thick.
Reduce heat.
Add 1 tablespoon strawberry jello powder and stir.
Cook 1 minute.
Add fresh strawberries.
Stir.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Refrigerate. Serve with whipped topping.

title: oven-fried chicken with sauce
directions: Combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper, stirring well; dredge chicken in flour mixture.
Set aside.
Pour butter into 13x9x2 baking pan.
Place chicken in pan, turning to coat with butter.

Cover and bake, meaty side down at 400° for 30 minutes. Turn chicken pieces, and pour Honey-Butter Sauce over each piece. Bake uncovered an additional 25 to 30 minutes or until tender, basting occasionally with sauce.

title: pot pie crust
directions: Use for vegetable meat pies or fruit cobblers.
Stir flour and sugar together.
Add other ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 11-inch pan or dish and then pour fruit or meat and vegetables.
Add a little butter on top.
Bake at 350° until nice and brown.

title: cracker spread
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Stir until well blended, then add next 7 ingredients.
Add the olive juice and combine all into the soft cream cheese.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Thoroughly mix peanut butter and margarine.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Add in sugar and mix, using hands.
Mix until mixture will not stick to hands.
Pinch off bits and roll in balls the size of small marbles.
Chill.

title: house salad
directions: Tear into bite size pieces and combine in a large bowl the 2 heads of lettuce.
Slice onion into thin slices.
Mix in drained green olives, pimentos and quartered artichoke hearts.
Mix red wine vinegar, canola oil, salt and pepper in jar.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and crushed bananas.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour or until firm and brown.

title: homemade alfredo sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine butter, heavy cream and cream cheese. Simmer until melted and mixed well. Add Parmesan cheese and garlic powder. Simmer on low for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Drop oil from salmon and clean to remove any bones.
Place salmon in large mixing bowl.
Add cubed bread.
Add other ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Pan-fry on both sides in canola oil or broil in oven.
Makes 4 patties.

title: dilled chicken salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Drain immediately and rinse with cold water until cool.
In medium size mixing bowl, toss the macaroni, spinach, chicken and peppers together.
Pour the dressing over salad and toss.
Garnish with orange slices.
Chill before serving.

title: butterscotch morsels
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch chips on low fire.
Add peanuts and shoestring potatoes and stir.
Place on a cookie sheet and freeze for one hour.
Break into small pieces to store.

title: norsk lappe(straight from the recipes of tante magnhild, flekkefjord,
directions: Beat the egg.
Add the sugar.
Dissolve baking soda in the buttermilk.
Add alternately to egg.
Mix with 1 cup flour.
At this point, recipe can be halved.
Beat well.
Beat in another cup of flour and another cup of buttermilk.
Drop by generous spoonfuls onto hot griddle or frypan.
Turn to cook both sides evenly.
Serve warm with butter and syrup or jam.
Or, serve cold with homemade preserves.

title: dog ears
directions: Spread dried beef with Philadelphia cream cheese (spread). Roll around a dill pickle.
Put in refrigerator.
Cut in slices just before serving.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions in butter until translucent.
Remove from heat. Add milk, eggs, and seasonings.
Add cheese.
Mix and pour into pie crust. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: calypso beets
directions: Heat to boiling: pineapple, beet juice and vinegar.
Mix cornstarch and sugar and add to liquid.
Cook until thickened. Add drain beets, butter and salt.
Serve hot.

title: mama's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix the ingredients and shape into loaf. Bake in 9 x 13 inch glass dish uncovered for one hour. Do not overcook. Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy way lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna
until tender.
Brown hamburger in skillet with salt, pepper, onion
and
garlic
to taste.
Set aside to cool. Thoroughly cook
sausage in skillet.
Cool and cut into small pieces.

title: prize winning persimmon pudding
directions: Cream pulp and sugar and add beaten eggs, beating well.
Put soda into buttermilk and salt until foaming ceases.
Add to pulp mixture alternately with dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
When all is blended, add the cream and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: homemade finger paint
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl, adding hot water.
Stir until smooth.
Put in a small container with cover and add a very small amount of coloring.
Mix well and cover for storage.
Finger paints may be used in several colors to make beautiful gift wrapping paper.
Glazed shelf paper or white freezer wrapping paper may be used for finger paint projects.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pam a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour ingredients in casserole.
Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato yam and apple casserole
directions: Layer yams and apples, end up, in a casserole dish with yams on top and bottom.

title: lemon chicken(djaj mtabbel)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl, coating chicken pieces well.
Marinate in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours, turning chicken over several times during this period.
Heat oven to 450°. Place chicken in baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour in the marinating mixture, basting occasionally.
Remove chicken pieces onto a serving dish.
Pour marinade over chicken pieces.
Serve with Tabouli, Zucchini-Potato Stew and Rice Pilaf.

title: easy homemade soup
directions: In a large saucepan, mix ingredients; stir well and add water to desired thickness.
Heat on medium heat until it simmers.
Lower heat and simmer covered for 1 to 2 hours.
Add salt and pepper to desired taste.

title: chocolate walnut pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the eggs, syrup, chocolate, margarine, cornstarch, vanilla and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. (Do not overbake; filling should be slightly less set in center.)

title: sugar cookies
directions: Roll out on floured board.
Cut out and bake.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla, butter and almond flavoring plus egg whites.
Gradually add confectioners sugar, beating well on medium speed.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often.
When all of the sugar has been mixed in, icing will appear dry.
Add milk and beat at high speed until light and fluffy.
Keep icing covered with a damp cloth until you are ready to decorate.
For best results, keep icing bowl in refrigerator when not in use.
Icing can be refrigerated in airtight container for 1 week, rewhip before using.

title: meat loaf with filling
directions: Mix all but bread crumbs.
Put half in ungreased pan.
Place crumbs on top of meat.
Cover with remaining meat.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: hot hominy casserole
directions: Drain hominy.
Brown sausage and drain.
Brown onions and pepper in butter. Add hominy, tomatoes, sausage and seasoning. Stir and cook for 20 minutes.
Layer in casserole dish, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Hamburger may be used instead of sausage.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, condensed milk, pineapple, lemon juice, pecan meal and sugar together.
Pour into pie shells and chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: prunola(u.s.a.)
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Add sugar, milk, rice, prunes and peanut butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 1/3 cup sugar gradually and continue beating.
Add vanilla.
Fold meringue carefully into the mixture; pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake in slow oven, 250°, for about 1 hour.
Serve with cream.

title: apple oat crumble
directions: Mix apples and honey.
Place in baking dish.
Spread oats on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 3 to 5 minutes.
Mix oats with remaining ingredients.
Spread over apple mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet relish
directions: Grind cabbage, red peppers, green peppers, onions, tomatoes and hot peppers.
Put in large enameled pan.
Sprinkle enough salt over vegetables like you were going to eat it raw.
Let set two hours.
Drain off green water.
Mix vinegar, water, sugar and black pepper.
Put celery and mustard seed in white bag; put in vinegar mixture and bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetable mixture and cook about 35 minutes.
Stir often.
Put in jars and seal.

title: watermelon lemonade
directions: Blend melon and raspberries in blender and strain very good. Discard pulp.
Stir in sugar and lemon juice and chill.

title: pie shell
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Cut shortening with pastry blender or 2 knives.
Sprinkle water over mixture.
Round into ball and roll out on a lightly floured board 1 1/2 inches larger than inverted 8-inch pie pan.
Place loosely in pie pan.
Fold edge under or over to make stand-up collar.
Prick thoroughly with a fork to prevent puffing.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 475°.

title: pork and potato casserole
directions: Layer into casserole dish: meat, layer of spuds, carrots, onions and leeks.
Make 3 of these layers.
Top with sliced tomatoes.
Pour white wine over the top.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mock corn bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 400° until done.
This bread is very good for people who can't eat corn bread.

title: fruit salad
directions: Clean strawberries and slice.
Combine all ingredients and stir.
Make sure the pineapple juice covers the bananas to keep them from turning color.
You may add other fruit, if you want to.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Add all spices with 3 cups of mayonnaise.
Add diced potatoes; add more mayonnaise to desired consistency and chill.

title: country supper casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in Wesson oil.
When brown, pour off oil. Place in casserole (3-quart), salt and pepper (mix into meat). Pour 1 can of tomato sauce over meat.
Arrange beans and carrots over meat.
Spoon mashed potatoes around edge of casserole.
Pour other can of tomato sauce over.
Bake in 350° oven 1/2 hour or until potatoes are browned.

title: tennessee lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sauce alfredo(serves 4)
directions: In a heavy saucepan, heat the butter and cream almost to a simmer.
Do not let it bubble.
Remove from heat and pour over cooked and drained pasta of your choice.
Toss with cheese, egg yolks, salt and pepper and nutmeg.
Serve immediately.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Mix cake according to box directions in jellyroll pan (16 x 11).
Let cool.

title: egg casserole
directions: Separate eggs.
Whip whites in copper bowl, if available.
If whites won't stiffen to peaks, beat in pinch of cream of tartar. Spoon whipped whites to perimeter of toast.
Layer on Canadian bacon.
Arrange egg yolks on top of bacon.
Bake at 350° to 370° until desired doneness is reached.
Ladle Hollandaise over dish. Top off with grated cheese.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour until blended; stir in slowly the cream.
When sauce is thick, stir in catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Remove shells and clean 1 pound of cooked shrimp.
Add to the sauce; stir together until they are well heated.
Season with salt, paprika and a few grains of cayenne pepper.
Immediately before serving, add 2 tablespoons sherry.
Serve in a grits ring or over rice.

title: shang hi
directions: Cook chicken.
Pick from bones.
In the broth, add the egg noodles, salt and pepper to taste and cream of mushroom.
Cook on top of stove.
When done, cover with cheese.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Boil water and raisins for 5 minutes and cool.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Cream together the shortening, sugar and egg.
Add raisin mixture to dry ingredients.
Fill 3 medium cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: harvard beets(a favorite recipe)
directions: Stir and cook until clear, all ingredients, except beets. Then add the beets, 2 tablespoons of butter and 1 or 2 tablespoons of orange marmalade.
Chill before serving.

title: no bake pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with nuts and maraschino cherries, if desired.
Chill 2 hours.

title: lily cookies
directions: Soften and cream together the cream cheese and butter.
Add the flour; mix well.
Roll out on wax paper; cut with a 2-inch round cookie cutter.
Roll rounds into cornucopia shape.
Press gently; shape like a lily.
Fill open part with jam; place cookies on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes, or until lightly brown.
Cool; drench pointed end in sugar.
Best with pineapple jam.

title: crunchy bacon coleslaw
directions: Mix mayo and sugar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add rice. Add hot broth and boil, covered, 25 minutes on low heat. Remove bay leaf and press into 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
Keep warm and unmold to serve.

title: purple cow
directions: Mix grape juice and vanilla ice cream together.
Drink it or eat it with a spoon.

title: quick 'n good stir-fry
directions: In heated skillet, add oil or drippings and onion.
Saute onion.
Add green beans and cabbage.
Stir often.
When cabbage starts to wilt, add bacon and season to taste.
Stir and serve.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 30 minutes after removing from the refrigerator.

title: fruit delight cake(dump or crumb cake)
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread pineapple on bottom of dish and pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle all of dry cake mix over pie filling.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Slice oleo about 1/4 inch thick and put all over top.
Sprinkle brown sugar over oleo.
Bake about 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: keflus
directions: Let stand 1 hour; divide into 6 parts.
Into 6 balls, wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out into pie crust form. Makes 16 pieces.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: holiday ornaments
directions: Mix and roll like cookie dough.
Mix real good.
Use cookie cutters.
Make small
hole to put hanger in before they dry.
Let dry 2 to 3 days.
Makes 12 to 15 ornaments.

title: ground beef enchiladas
directions: Brown the ground beef in a skillet, then add the onion and brown some more until the onion is brown. Add enchilada sauce, mushroom soup and chicken soup. Stir well to mix ingredients. Set aside.

title: german potato salad
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until
crisp; drain and crumble, reserving
cup drippings.
Cook
onion
in
the
reserved drippings until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour, sugar, celery seed and pepper.
Add vinegar and 1 cup of water.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir
in
bacon, potatoes and eggs. Heat through,
tossing
lightly.
Garnish
with	parsley,
if desired. Serves 8 to 10.

title: french coqauvin(chicken in red wine sauce)
directions: Heat olive oil in large saucepan or wok.
Clean chicken pieces and pat dry.
Add to hot oil, turning frequently, until browned. Season with salt and pepper.

title: amber's favorite mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together. Bake in skillet at 350° for 1 hour or spoon into muffin pan and bake for 35 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to the egg mixture with crushed bananas. Fold in nuts and raisins, if desired.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar with a hand mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry and drain bacon; crumble and set aside.
Combine egg, flour, sugar, vinegar and water in a medium frypan.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add bacon and salt if needed. Serve over dandelion or lettuce.

title: chocolate chip kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.

In a large bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff. Gradually add sugar and vanilla. Fold in chocolate chips and pecans. Spoon by heaping teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet lined with heavy brown paper.
Bake 45 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine together crushed graham crackers and powdered sugar, then mix in melted butter and peanut butter.
Smooth mixture on the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted semi-sweet chocolate over the top.
Refrigerate until chocolate is hard.
Cut into small squares.

title: grandma's gumdrop cookies
directions: Mix first eight ingredients together.
Stir in gumdrops. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook
rice
according
to
directions on package.
Cook broccoli
according
to
directions on package.
Combine soups and Cheez
Whiz; heat until bubbly.
Put rice in the bottom of a long baking
dish.
Stir in broccoli, soups and Cheez Whiz. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: country style steak
directions: Place Crisco in frying pan.
Roll pieces of steak in flour. Salt and pepper, then fry until lightly browned all steak.
Remove from frying pan.
Place in layers in baking dish.
Cover with water to top of steak.
Cover with foil and place in oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
This time will depend on tenderness of steak, but will end up making its own gravy.

title: banana split
directions: Mix crumbs and melted butter together and pat into bottom of a medium size dish.
Beat together sugar, softened butter, eggs and vanilla and pour over first mixture.
Alternately layer pineapple, bananas, Cool Whip and crushed nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: busy day casserole
directions: In a large skillet, add oil, onion and green pepper.
Saute until tender-crisp.
Add ground beef.
Stir to brown evenly. Drain.

title: baked pork chops(yield: 6 servings)
directions: Place chops in baking pan in single layer; salt and pepper to taste.
Spread 2 teaspoons of brown sugar and 2 tablespoons of ketchup on each chop.
Top with slice of onion and slice of lemon. Add enough water to reach a level halfway up on chops.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Uncover the last half hour of cooking.

title: easy freezer pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat until cucumbers change from dark green to light dull green.
(Just a few minutes after sugar melts.)
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Next day, place in freezer cups or Ziploc bags.
If Ziploc bags are used, thaw before serving and put in Mason jar to keep in refrigerator.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix ingredients well and fill buns with tuna mixture.
Wrap filled buns into 8 pieces of aluminum foil.
Put foil wrapped buns on a cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick and easy peas
directions: Drain peas.
Saute onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients; heat and serve.
You may put this in a buttered casserole, top with grated Cheddar cheese and bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: christmas cheese star
directions: Line a 1-quart star-shaped mold with plastic wrap.
In a large bowl, combine cheeses, pimientos, onion, garlic powder and red pepper using an electric mixer.
Spoon into prepared mold.
Cover and chill 1 hour. Invert mold onto a serving plate.
Remove plastic wrap.
Use a small star-shaped aspic cutter to cut out stars from sweet red pepper.
Garnish cheese star with cucumber slices, red pepper stars and parsley.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to present.
Give with serving instructions.
Yield: about 3 3/4 cups cheese spread.

title: cooked squash
directions: Fry pork side in a skillet over low/medium heat until tender. (This is to season the squash.)
Saute onion lightly in skillet with pork.
Remove pork from skillet and add cut squash in about 1/8-inch thick slices.
Cover with water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough to 12x9 inch rectangle on lightly floured surface.
Combine oregano and garlic powder; mix with olive oil.
Brush oil mixture lightly on dough, reserving some for top.
Cover with pepperoni and cheese.
Roll up jellyroll style.
Brush with remaining oil.
Pinch seams tightly.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes. Cool at least 15 minutes before slicing into 1 inch slices.

title: ann lindler's sweet potato pone
directions: Grate sweet potatoes.
Mix all ingredients, except eggs and potatoes.
Beat eggs well; add and then fold in potatoes.
Bake in deep dish, until firm, in 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: breakfast club munch
directions: Mix in a bowl peanuts, sunflower seeds, raisins and M&M's. Add Cheerios.
Stir gently
Serve in paper cups.

title: frozen salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in pineapple juice over low heat; cool. Add salad dressing and pineapple, then food color. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into molds or ice cube tray and freeze.

title: v.b.s.  oatmeal cookies
directions: In very large bowl, beat until creamy first 6 ingredients. In another large bowl, sift together flour, salt and soda; add to creamy mixture.
Mix well, then add oatmeal and nuts.
Mix well with wooden spoon; drop onto ungreased cookie sheet, flatten with fork.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 360° (for chewy cookies, bake less time).
Yield:
10 dozen.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Place oil in skillet and add chicken strips, onion, bell pepper; saute.
Add tomatoes and water, salt and pepper, garlic and potatoes.
Cook on medium heat for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli (do not overcook).
Mix mayonnaise, curry powder, lemon juice
and soup together.
Do not add any water. Use 9 x
9-inch casserole dish or larger.
Alternate layers of broccoli, chicken
and
sauce.
Cover
top	with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: diabetic oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, raisins and oatmeal. Mix well.
Beat in replacement sugar, melted margarine, egg and skim milk.
Add small amounts of water if dough is too stiff.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: washington state apple pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine apples, water and lemon juice; cook over medium-low heat just until the apples are tender.
Remove from the heat and cool (do not drain).

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter; add sugar; blend in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients. Stir into other batter.
Roll in balls the size of walnut.
Drop balls in cinnamon and sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: jewish potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Skin off peelings gently while potatoes are still hot.
Carefully slice potatoes as thin as possible, still having consistency.
Pour oil and vinegar over potatoes.
Mix evenly, trying not to break potatoes.
Add well chopped dill pickles, using shredder.
Add onion to taste. Finally add salt and pepper and large spoonful or two of mayonnaise.

title: modeling dough
directions: Mix Bisquick, salt and cream of tartar in a microwavable 4-cup glass measuring cup.
Mix water and food color in a liquid measuring cup.
Stir liquid into the dry mixture, a little at a time, until all the liquid is added.
Microwave, uncovered, on High (100°) for 1 minute.
Scrape the mixture from the side of the cup and stir.
Microwave, uncovered, on High (100°) for 2 to 3 minutes longer, stirring every minute, until the mixture forms sort of a ball.
Let the dough stand, uncovered, about 3 minutes. Spoon out of the measuring cup.
Knead in your hands or on the counter about 1 minute or until smooth.
Cool about 15 minutes. Use to make your favorite shapes and designs.
Place in a tightly covered container or plastic bag; refrigerate.
Makes about 1/2 pound.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Mix water and gelatin until softened.
Chop shrimp and vegetables fine.
Whip cream cheese until soft and creamy.
Add gelatin and soup, blending well.
Stir in mayonnaise and vegetables.
Add seasonings and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into oiled 4-cup mold; refrigerate overnight.
Unmold on pretty platter.
Serve with crackers.

title: malia's salad dressing
directions: Mix in order given.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: green chili chicken soup
directions: Bring all ingredients, except chicken to a boil and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add chicken during last half hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thinly slice the potatoes (about 1/4-inch thick is best); then add to salted boiling water.
Cover, boil 5 minutes; drain.

title: moist and creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes.
Poke holes down through cake with a toothpick.

title: chili dip ole(microwave)
directions: Crumble ground beef into medium glass bowl.
Stir in onion. Cook at High 3 to 4 minutes, or until beef is browned; stir once. Drain.
Stir in chili seasoning, tomato paste and sugar.
Cook at High 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve warm with corn chips.
Yields 2 cups.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, and sugar until fluffy and light.
Add well beaten eggs.
Combine flour and baking powder, and add to creamed mixture.
Add milk alternately with flavoring.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan, for 1 1/2 hours at 300 to 325 degrees.

title: corned beef mold
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Then mix jello in hot water.
Add to ring.
Spray mold with Pam and chill.
Serve on crackers.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water; cool.
Add other ingredients. Chill.
Serves 6.

title: preserving children
directions: Combine children with dogs.
Empty into the field, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle the field with flowers.
Pour the brook over the pebbles.
Cover all with deep blue sky.
Bake in the hot sun until children are well browned and tired.
Remove children to bathtub to cool.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Pan-fry beef and onion until light brown and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: texas banana cake
directions: Mix with spoon. Combine all dry ingredients; add the rest and mix well. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown. Delicious plain with coffee or use your favorite icing. This cake slices better the next day and stays moist.

title: peking roast
directions: Cut slits completely through the meat and insert sliver of garlic alternating with onion in next slit.
(Can use all onion if you do not like garlic.)
Pour vinegar over meat, making sure it gets into the slits.
Place in refrigerator and leave for 24 to 48 hours.
When ready to cook, place in heavy roaster or pot and brown very well on all sides.
Pour in coffee and water and cover. Simmer on top of stove 4 to 6 hours.
Season with salt and pepper 20 minutes before serving.
This roast falls apart at the touch of a fork.
Drippings can be thickened or used as they are.

title: frosted chocolate brownies
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed of an electric mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat well.
Add egg whites, sour cream, milk and vanilla extract.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in small bowl.
Add flour mix to creamed mix.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Spread frosting on cooled brownies.
Cut into squares.
Yields 24 servings (183 calories; 19% from fat).

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef in skillet; add tomato sauce.
Line 9-inch plate with biscuits and cooked mixture.
Top with cheese.
Cook at 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: homemade sherbet
directions: Mix ingredients
together
and freeze.	Put in blender, then refreeze.
For
best results, use fresh orange or tangerine juice. If canned juice is used, cut sugar amount.

title: hungarian popovers(kati felfujtja)
directions: The wood stove sat in the middle of the church.
We would all take out chairs and huddle around the stove for warmth.
The patched hole for the flue can still be seen in the ceiling.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook in lightly greased and floured Bundt cake pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: puddin cookies
directions: Mix.
Form into small balls.
Flatten with hand on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Cut meat
in serving size pieces.
Combine all ingredients, covering meat well.
Put in roasting pan.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Uncover and bake an additional 1/2 hour for meat to brown.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream brown and white sugar, eggs and the salad oil in one pan. In another pan, mix the flour, baking powder, salt, nuts, oats, soda, coconut and chips.
Combine the two mixtures in a large pan (dishpan).
Drop by small spoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
This will make 15 to 18 dozen cookies (ideal for Vacation Bible School or a party where several cookies are needed).

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into 9 in. pan and bake in pre-heated 350° oven for 1 hr.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, butter, eggs and spices.
Add potatoes and milk.
Stir well.
Pour in baking dish.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add bananas and nuts.
Mix flour and soda.
Add to other ingredients.
Pour in slightly greased bread pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken italian style
directions: Brown chicken in preheated nonstick skillet.
Add pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook 4 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.

title: apple crisp pie
directions: Place apple slices in unbaked pie shell.
Mix dry ingredients together well and add to apples, making sure it goes down into apples.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Prepare the envelope of Dream Whip.
Mix in cottage cheese and unprepared Jell-O.
Mix in crushed pineapple.
Chill until ready to eat.

title: dill dip
directions: Make at least 8 hours before serving. Serve with chips.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cut tortillas in 1-inch strips.
Mix all other ingredients and layer tortillas and mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with additional cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Set aside cucumbers and onions.
Cook vinegar, water, sugar, salt and celery seed until it comes to a boil.
Put cucumbers and onions in until they change color.
Set aside to cool.
Put in jars and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: mom's carrot and raisin salad
directions: Chop up carrots and toss with raisins.
Blend the remaining ingredients together and pour over carrots and raisins.
Stir and chill.

title: death by chocolate(serves 16+)
directions: Bake cake as directed using 9 x 14-inch pan. Cool slightly. Poke holes throughout entire cake.
Pour Amaretto over cake and cover.
Place cake in refrigerator overnight.
Cut cake into 3 x 1-inch pieces.
Make cook-style chocolate pudding.
Cool.
Crush Skor bars in a blender or food processor.
Layer 2 times in a clear bowl 1/2 cake pieces, 1/2 pudding, 1/2 Skor bars, 1/2 whipped cream.
Repeat.
Decorate with chocolate shavings, strawberries with mint leaves.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat oil with sugar.
Blend in beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Add nuts and carrots, small amount at a time.
Blend well.
Bake in three greased pans or 10-inch tube pan or sheet pan at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour, depending on thickness of pan.

title: fluff fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save 1 cup juice in a small pan.
Set aside the pineapple.
To pan of juice, add sugar, flour, eggs, orange juice, lemon juice and oil.
Boil 1 minute; remove from heat and let cool.
In salad bowl, combine pineapple, fruit cocktail, oranges and bananas.
Fold in cream and cooled sauce.
Chill for several hours.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into strips 3 inches long.
Wash, quarter and remove seeds; cut 1/2 strips.
Heat oil in skillet; lightly brown meat. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic.
Add green peppers, celery and onions, stirring.
Prevent sticking.
Add beef broth and cook, covered, over low heat 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and Worcestershire sauce together and add to meat mixture until sauce thickens.
Serve over hot rice.

title: escalloped vegetables
directions: Melt butter. Add flour and cook on medium 2 minutes.
Remove and stir in milk. Cook until thick.
Add cheese and stir. Add salt to taste.
Combine vegetables and sauce.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots; drain and cool.
Cut onion and pepper in round slices.
Mix with cool carrots.
Mix other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate 12 hours or more.
Drain to serve.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 weeks.

title: creamed corn chicken
directions: Fry chicken in grease until brown on both sides.
Put in baking dish and dice up the fresh tomatoes.
Spread on top of chicken.
Pour the can of creamed corn over everything Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: lemon cheesecake in 15 minutes
directions: Stir cream cheese until very soft.
Gradually blend in 1/2 cup milk until smooth and creamy.
Add remaining milk and the pudding mix.
Beat slowly with egg beater 1 minute.
(Do not overbeat.) Pour into cooled graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top to make it extra crunchy, then chill.
That's all, really.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, Miracle Whip and chili powder.
Layer one-half each of meat mixture, chips and cheese in 2-quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers and bake 20 minutes until hot.
Top with lettuce and tomato, if desired.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in melted chocolate, then flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 350 for 10 minutes.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Cut okra into small slices. Chop onion, green tomato and bell pepper and fry in oil until oil returns to clear stage. Mash whole tomatoes into this mixture and cook for about 10 minutes longer. Season ground chuck with salt and pepper. Mix other chopped onion with this. Form meat into balls. Cut sausage into 1/2-inch slices. Add meat balls and sausage to a pot of boiling water. Add okra and other vegetables and let simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: tuna mushroom casserole
directions: Put in a large Corning Ware dish or pan the mushroom soup, evaporated milk and tuna.
Cook until it thickens.
Pour into casserole dish and put a can of prepared biscuits on top.
Bake until biscuits are done.
If you want mixture thicker, add flour while cooking but be sure to cook long enough for flour to get done.

title: strawberry chiffon
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in strawberries and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thick.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill until set, about 2 hours.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Layer bottom of 9 x 13 pan with Crispy Crowns potatoes. Brown hamburger; add broccoli, cream of celery soup and 2 cups shredded Cheddar cheese.
Pour hamburger mix over potatoes.
Top with Durkee fried onions and chopped tomato.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 minutes.
Last 10 minutes, top with 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: apple butter
directions: Peel apples and slice. Cook with a little water. Stir often. After cooking awhile, put in a blender and measure pulp. Add rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil and cook for 15 minutes. Pour in clean hot jars and seal.

title: delicious salad dressing
directions: Mix together and shake in a jar.

title: jello toast
directions: Butter bread and sprinkle with dry jello.
Excellent with bowl of hot cereal.
For variety, use hamburger or hot dog buns.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and 1/2 cup of the melted oleo in large bowl. Add onion, sour cream, soup and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix the remaining 1/2 cup melted oleo with corn flakes.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 4 layer pie
directions: Mix flour and melted butter.
Spread on bottom of square pan. Top with pecans.
Bake until brown.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread over flour mixture.
Mix pudding with milk. Spread on cream cheese.
Top with Cool Whip.
Let chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger, green peppers, onions and basil together. heat tomato sauce and tomatoes together until hot.
Cook rice as per directions.
Mix hamburger mixture with tomatoes and rice and let heat on low for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger, rice and cheese
directions: Fry hamburger meat and drain.
Meanwhile, fix Minute rice according to box.
Mix all these together; add cheese and seasoned salt to taste.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into patties and fry in hot vegetable shortening until brown.

title: ginger beef noodle soup
directions: Brown ground beef, pour off drippings.
Add salt, ginger and pepper.
Stir in water, broth and seasoning package from noodles. Bring to a boil.
Stir in vegetables and noodles.
Return to boil. Cook until noodles are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given and bake in large loaf pan or 2 small pans at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple surprise
directions: Roll vanilla wafers into fine crumbs.
Divide crumbs into 3 parts.
Put 1/3 in bottom of square dish.
Beat butter, eggs and powdered sugar until creamy.
Pour over crumb layer.
On top of this mixture, place another layer of crumbs.
Whip 1 pint of cream into can of pineapple.
Pour cream and pineapple over second layer of crumbs.
Top with portion of crumbs.
Freeze overnight.
Whipped cream may be used for topping.

title: lemon chicken for the grill
directions: Place chicken in a large mixing bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Cook chicken over medium heat on outdoor grill for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Baste with marinade every 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crispy potato hamburger cakes
directions: Shred potatoes; add remaining ingredients except fat and mix thoroughly.
Makes 8 (3-inch) cakes.
Fry slowly in shallow fat.

title: oriental rice
directions: Cook rice until slightly underdone.
Saute green onions including tops, green pepper and celery.
Do not saute more than 3 or 4 minutes as they should be crunchy, not well done.
Add pimento and almonds.
While tossing rice, season generously with 3 or 4 tablespoons of soy sauce until the rice has a brown color; add Accent generously, sugar and pepper but no salt.
Mix the rice with the celery, pepper, onion, mushroom, pimento and almond mixture. Add cooked meat that has been cut up.
Cover and cook on very low heat until served.
Garnish with two flat fried eggs which have been sliced in thin slices.
This is great for a large crowd.
It can be prepared ahead of time.

title: hot potato salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Pan-fry bacon and crumble.
Boil potatoes in jackets, then peel and dice.
Put in
a large bowl.
Toss with rest of ingredients.
Put in buttered, large, uncovered casserole (or two smaller ones).
Top with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. May be made ahead; allow extra baking time.

title: ham ball
directions: Blend ham, olives, mustard and Tabasco sauce; form into balls on serving dish.
Chill.
Combine cream cheese and milk; frost ball with mixture.
Chill.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: crab cakes
directions: In a small mixing bowl stir together the egg whites, 1/3 cup bread crumbs, green onion, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Stir in crabmeat.
In a shallow dish, toss the 1/4 cup bread crumbs with melted margarine.

title: brent's baked beans
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffing balls
directions: Cube bread.
Saute onion and celery until limp (not brown) in oleo.
Add to bread.
Add 1/2 can of soup, thyme and pepper.
Mix well.
Form into 12 balls.
Place in a greased baking dish.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In blender or food processor, chop cranberries and orange. Add sugar and Jell-O.
Add one or all of the celery, pecans and apples.
Make a day ahead and let set.

title: lemon cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let cool.
Add cake mix, oil and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Prick holes in top of hot cake and pour glaze over it.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add oil, coffee and milk; mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 2 more minutes.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool cakes 15 minutes before removing from pans.
Use Missionary Icing.

title: ann's linguini salad
directions: After cooking linguini, rinse with cold water.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Use all of the salad seasoning and all of the Italian dressing.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for 6 hours.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir constantly until jello is thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using wire whip, blend in Cool Whip.
Whip until smooth.
Fold in fruit and chill.

title: strawberry-lemon tart
directions: Prepare pastry for 10-inch tart pan.
Roll to a 12-inch circle and place in tart pan that has a removable bottom.
Prick the pastry and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: breakfast sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage, drain.
Place in pie shell.
Sprinkle grated cheese, flour, and onion on top.
Beat eggs and milk; pour over mixture in pie shell.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: pineapple - 7-up - lemon salad
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in boiling water.
Add 7-Up and chill. Add crushed pineapple, bananas and marshmallows; refrigerate until firm.

title: apple cake
directions: Grease 12 cup microwave Bundt cake pan.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle pan thoroughly with sugar mixture.
Stir together cake mix, eggs, sour cream and apple pie filling.
Hand mix.
Pour into cake pan and spread evenly.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave on High 9 minutes, giving cake a turn halfway and cook 9 minutes longer.
After cooking let cake stand 10 minutes before inverting onto cake platter.
Cool cake and drizzle with glaze if desired.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Mix cottage cheese, spinach, egg, salt, oregano, basil, pepper, parsley and 2 cups cheese in mixing bowl.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread just enough sauce to cover bottom of pan.
Place noodles in bottom (uncooked).
Cover with 1/2 of the cottage cheese mixture and some spaghetti sauce.
Place more noodles on top of that and repeat process.
Place last noodles on top and cover with remaining spaghetti and cheese.
Pour 1/2 cup water into pan, cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes more. Serve.

title: mom's quick family meal
directions: Cook Pennsylvania Dutch egg noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add butter/margarine to preference.
While noodles are cooking brown ground meat with onion, Accent, Italian seasoning and garlic salt; drain.
Add to cooked buttered noodles; cover.
Microwave or heat up peas and mushrooms; drain.
Add to noodle mixture.
Combine ingredients well and serve with buttered bread or rolls.

title: fried pie crusts
directions: Mix all.
Put in refrigerator until cold.
Pinch out enough for each pie and roll on floured sheet.
Cut by a saucer, before adding fruit (apples and peaches).
Cook in greased hot skillet.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Bring to boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until onion is tender.

title: butterfingers
directions: Put 1 teaspoon of peanut butter in between 2 Triscuits and dip in dipping chocolate.
Set on waxed paper.
Fourteen ounces of dipping chocolate and 24 Triscuits equals 12 Butterfingers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine chopped pecans, butter, vanilla, sugar, eggs and syrup.
Pour into pie shell; bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Arrange pecan halves on top of pie filling.
Reduce heat; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Bake slowly.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Use whole cucumbers or slice large cucumbers lengthwise.
Wash and dry pickles.
Put in crock or gallon jar.
Mix ingredients into cold vinegar and pour over pickles.
These are best after set a few days.
You may have to stir them.
Open.
Do not can.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain juice from pears and add enough water to make 3 cups liquid.
Heat and dissolve the Jell-O.
Cool in refrigerator until thick.
Whip, then add cream cheese which has been softened with a small amount of pear juice.
Fold in the pears and whipped cream. Add nuts if desired.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except lemon juice in 4-quart saucepan.
Heat until steaming.
Stir in lemon juice and serve.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix
all ingredients and place in buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until puffed.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip; blend well.
Spoon into crust.
Top with a can of cherry pie filling.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: steak marinade
directions: Place in blender soy sauce, onions and garlic.
Process in blender for 1 minute.
Stir in gravy coloring and seasoning. Arrange steaks or chops in a shallow glass dish.
Pour 1/2 cup for each steak.
Let stand for 2 hours or refrigerate overnight. Bring to room temperature before grilling.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream butter, cheese and flour.
Roll and cut in small biscuits.
Dip one side of biscuit in beaten egg (or brush with a pastry brush).
Place 1/2 pecan on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Stir in flour; add water.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Blend in cheese until melted.

title: garlic cheese dip
directions: Blend thoroughly with electric mixer or food processor. Serve at room temperature with crackers or vegetables.

title: garlic herb spread
