directions: In large food processor, with chopping blade, process first five ingredients until finely chopped.
Add cream cheese, butter, Worcestershire, and vinegar; process just until well mixed and creamy.
Line a 1 1/4-quart plastic container or shallow bowl with plastic wrap. Spread mixture into container. Refrigerate.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan. You may add more apples if you wish, but mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Batter is real thick, but it is good.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown bacon until half done.
Chop and saute onion.
Brown hamburger.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, prepared mustard, butter beans, kidney beans and pork and beans. Put all in crock-pot.
Cook on low several hours.
Great for large party!

title: lasagna #1
directions: In bottom of baking dish, spoon lasagna sauce to cover bottom. Layer lasagna noodles, garden sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layering until done.
Cover with foil. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake, uncovered, for 20 more minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting. Serves 6 to 8.

title: caesar salad
directions: Rub wooden salad bowl with garlic pieces.
Pare and chop lettuce.
Add to salad bowl.
In another bowl, mix Parmesan cheese, pepper, oil, lemon juice, salt and mustard.
Blend well. Pour over lettuce and toss well.
Add croutons and additional freshly grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
(Note:
To make own croutons; saute cubes of bread in olive oil, flavored with garlic.)

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixer bowl and mix well. Bake in greased and floured tube pan in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes or two 9-inch layer pans for 25 minutes.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in pan, heat until bubbling.
Remove from heat, add peanut butter and chow mein noodles, mix.
Drop from spoon onto wax paper.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Saute onions, garlic, green pepper and celery until onions are clear.
Add 1/8 cup water.
Cook until vegetables are done (about 15 minutes).
Add crawfish meat and fat.
Cover and cook 15 minutes on low fire.
Stir occasionally.
Add rest of ingredients, taking cornstarch, stirring in about 1/2 cup water until well dissolved.
Cook 5 minutes more. Serves 4 to 5. Cajun's serve this one over cooked rice, but it's a great dip.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff like meringue, then add sugar and beat again until like meringue.
Add the chocolate chips, vanilla and salt.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet covered with foil.
Put in preheated oven at 350°.
Close door immediately; turn off oven.
Leave cookies in oven overnight.

title: potato fingers
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water until done.
Mash the potatoes. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Roll potato dough mixture into the form of long sausages.
Slice the dough sausages into 2 to 3-inch lengths.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine bread, apples and raisins (if desired).
In a medium mixing bowl, beat eggs at medium speed. Add half and half, apple juice concentrate and melted butter, mixing well.
Add sugar, vanilla and cinnamon and mix well.
Place 1/2 of bread mixture in a large, deep-dish casserole sprayed with nonstick cooking spray and pour 1/2 of egg mixture over it.
With spoon, gently press bread pieces down into mixture to coat them. Repeat with remaining bread and egg mixtures.
Cover and let stand 30 minutes, preheating oven to 350° while mixture is standing. Place in oven and bake, covered, for about 40 to 45 minutes or until egg mixture is set but not too dry.
Remove from oven and let cool 15 minutes before serving.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, cocoa and milk in a saucepan and bring to a boil for exactly 3 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients; mix well and spoon onto wax paper.

title: cool ranch potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cube.
Place in casserole dish and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until potatoes are soft.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix and chill before serving.
Keeps well in refrigerator for several days.
Serves 8.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Combine flour, sugar and undissolved yeast in large bowl. Gradually add warm water to dry ingredients and beat until smooth. Cover with transparent wrap and let stand in warm place for 2 days.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix.
Add bran. Mix water and bananas together and add.
Mix dry ingredients and add nuts, if wanted.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and then check with toothpick.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with potato chips or tortilla chips.

title: best ever pie crust
directions: Add Crisco, salt and flour.
Mix until well blended.
Place: egg, vinegar and water in small bowl and beat.
Add to flour mixture, work together.
Roll out.
Bake at 375° if oven is preheated or 425° if not.
Bake until golden brown.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: mexican beef sandwich rolls
directions: Cut tops off rolls and scoop out insides. Brown beef and onion.
Stir in olives, salsa, cumin and chili powder.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Fill each roll 3/4 full.
Sprinkle on a layer of each cheese.
Top with bacon slices.
Put top on roll and wrap each roll in foil.
Heat in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: Melt cheeses together; add garlic salt.
Overlap edges of chipped beef and spread mixture over beef.
Roll tightly and freeze until firm.

title: peanut butter shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until smooth.
Serve at once.

title: lemon pecan pie
directions: Mix in order given; pour in unbaked pie shell.
Preheat oven to 350°; bake for 10 minutes, then 10 minutes at 300°, until crust is brown.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and flavoring and beat well.
Add crushed potato chips and butterscotch chips.
Sift flour and soda together.
Stir into cream mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: plantation cornish hens
directions: Cut hens lengthwise into halves. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brush with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: annie's mexican corn bread
directions: Combine meal, eggs and milk; mix.
Add onion, peppers and corn. Brown hamburger; drain.
Pour 1/2 of the corn bread mixture into a warmed, greased skillet.
Layer hamburger and cheese on the mix in skillet.
Pour on the rest of the corn bread mix.
Bake at 350° until corn bread is done.

title: cabbage-burger bake
directions: *One and 1/2 pounds total.

title: cheesy pita pizza appetizers
directions: Lightly brush pita bread with Kraft Italian dressing.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Top each pita with 2 slices cheese and pizza toppings.
Drizzle with additional dressing.
Bake 1 or 2 minutes or until cheese begins to melt.
Cut into quarters.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: working girls rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into greased muffin pans (3/4 full).
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Store remaining batter in refrigerator, well covered.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes and let freshen in cold water before grating. Grate potatoes (coarsely) into mixing bowl.
Add well beaten eggs and mix thoroughly.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt which have been sifted together.	Add onion.

title: 1000 island dressing
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve on hearts of lettuce.

title: 4 layer blueberry pie
directions: 1st Layer:
Melt the margarine and add nuts and flour.
Mix well and press into a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: poor man's filet mignon
directions: Combine first seven ingredients and 2 tablespoons barbecue sauce.
Form into 12 thick patties, about 2/3 cup meat for each filet.
Wrap a bacon slice around the sides of each patty and secure with a toothpick.

title: tomatoes - scalloped
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender. Stir in bread crumbs in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Layer half the tomatoes.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar. Cover with half the crumb mixture. Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven french fries
directions: Peel the potatoes and cut into long strips, about 1/2-inch wide.
Dry strips thoroughly on paper towels. Put in a bowl with the oil.

title: stir-fry chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut chicken into 1/8-inch slices.
Heat wok or large skillet. Add oil.
Stir-fry chicken 5 to 6 minutes or until white and firm. Remove from wok.
Add peppers.
Stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms, garlic and onions.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Return chicken to wok.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over linguini.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cap, clean and drain strawberries.
Slice into thin slices. Mix strawberries and glaze together.
Mix cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk and fold in Cool Whip.

title: spinach salad with curry dressing
directions: Wash spinach; pinch off leaves and discard stems.
Pat the leaves dry on paper towels and wrap in towels and refrigerate until ready to use.
Slice onion in rings and separate.
Combine the oil, vinegar, wine, soy sauce, sugar, mustard, curry powder, salt and pepper in a jar with a tight fitting lid.
Shake until mixed.
The dressing can be made ahead.
Tear the spinach into bite size pieces; add onion and any other garnishes desired.
Toss with 3 or 4 tablespoons of dressing.
Enjoy!

title: 24 hour cold water dill pickles
directions: Boil water, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Bring to room temperature.
Crush a lot of garlic.
Add dill to jars.

title: velvet waffles
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Separate eggs and beat yolks until light.
Stir milk into them.
Add oil.
Stir mixture gradually into dry ingredients.
Beat well, then fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in waffle iron.
You may use 1 cup buttermilk with 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Also pecans added to batter is delicious!

title: easy and light pasta dinner
directions: Put chicken breasts in a long baking dish.
Pour over the chicken the next 3 ingredients.
Cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Last 10 minutes of baking, prepare pasta as directed on box.
Drain and butter pasta.
Serve chicken mixture over top.

title: after dinner mints
directions: Combine cream cheese and flavoring.
Add enough food coloring to desired color.
Add sugar gradually, mixing well.
Form into 1/2 to 1-inch balls.
Press down with thumb.
Place in container with waxed paper between layers.
Cover lightly.
May be frozen until ready to use.
Makes about 200 mints.

title: hash brown casserole # 2
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in large casserole dish and top

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix ingredients and cook for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Add jello with hot water, then add Comstock and nuts.
Let chill.
Add topping of sour cream, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over top; put in refrigerator and chill.
Best overnight in refrigerator.

title: cardamon braid
directions: Prepare hot roll mix according to package.
Add melted butter, cooled, to cardamon and raisins.
Mix well.
Cover.
Let rise until double (1 hour).
On lightly floured surface, knead dough about 1 minute; divide in thirds.
Roll each third underhand to form a strand 10-inches long, tapering ends.
Place strands 1 inch apart on greased baking sheet.
Beginning in middle, braid three strands loosely, working toward either end.
Pinch ends together.
Cover and let rise until almost double (40 minutes, approximately). Brush braid with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Bring margarine, light corn syrup, brown sugar and salt to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour mixture over 9 quarts of popped corn.
Bake mixture in large buttered roaster at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in oleo until tender; add water, broccoli, cubes and milk.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add cheese and cook for a few minutes.
Bring to a boil and thicken with cornstarch mixed in water.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Put berries in 9 x 12-inch pan, then sprinkle sugar over berries. Top with pineapple and then cake mix; add nuts. Drizzle margarine over mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Refrigerate.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine and stir in pudding, dry.
Before serving, add Cool Whip.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; heat on low until sugar dissolves; cool.
Chop broccoli and cauliflower and combine with bacon, onion and Cheddar cheese.
Pour dressing over salad and mix.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: fruit dip ii
directions: Mix well with mixer. Serve with strawberries, cantaloupe or honeydew melon.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Toast 1/2 cup coconut; set aside.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes; cool slightly.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add sweetened condensed milk, water, vanilla, salt and nutmeg; mix well.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup coconut.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°; bake 25 to 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool. Chill if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: Saute mushrooms and garlic in butter for 3 minutes.
Add noodles, sour cream, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir gently.
Transfer to oiled casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan and bake, covered, for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dill chicken and artichokes
directions: Pour salad dressing into a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Add chicken breasts to pan. Sprinkle salt, pepper and dill weed over chicken. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Top chicken with mushrooms and artichokes.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Wash peppers; remove seeds and drain on paper.
Layer peppers and cheese in casserole.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add salt, flour and evaporated milk; stir until smooth.
Add to beaten whites.
Pour over chili and cheese in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Mix in pineapple and pecans and fold into ice cream until dissolved. Pour into a large mold or several small ones.
Set in refrigerator to congeal.

title: peach and cream cheese pie
directions: Mix the flour, margarine, baking powder, salt, pudding, egg and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into a well-greased 10-inch pie pan. Place a layer of drained peaches on top of batter.
Beat until smooth, the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and peach juice.
Pour over top of peaches, spreading within 1/2 inch of edge of pan (important).
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello according to directions on box.
When jello is dissolved, mix all ingredients.
Pour in a bowl and chill.

title: canned pickled beets
directions: Boil
whole
beets
with 1-inch top stem and all of root for 1 hour; drain water and add cold water.
Slip skin off and quarter;
add even amounts of water, sugar and red vinegar; add a handful
of mixed pickle spice.
Bring to boil.
Boil slowly for 15
minutes.
Fill
jars
and
seal.
(Cover
pickles with water, sugar and vinegar.)

title: almond joy cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
While cake is baking, mix milk and 1 cup sugar; bring to a rapid boil.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Add coconut.
Pour over baked cake.
Place 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup canned milk and margarine in a pan.
Heat to a boil.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted and pour over cake.
Top with toasted almonds.

title: 5-minute devil's food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan; bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with Mountain Top Icing.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Beat eggs until light.
Add gradually to mixture.
Also add sugar. Beat light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with fruit cocktail undrained.
Mix until smooth after each addition.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup of brown sugar packed and 1/4 cup chopped nuts.
Sprinkle over cake until done.

title: frozen salad
directions: Line muffin tin with cupcake paper.
Mix all the ingredients. Fill cupcake papers with mixture and freeze.

title: oven-crisp sliced potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and place in a plastic bag (two at a time) with the Lipton soup mix and oil.
Shake to coat potatoes.
Place in baking dish or uncovered pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Should be crisp.
Serves 6.

title: clam chowder #2
directions: Saute bacon; drain off drippings.
Set aside.
Drain clams, reserving 1 cup juice; set clams aside.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar and frozen coconut and refrigerate overnight. Bake yellow cake mix according to package directions. Cool and cut into 4 layers.
Before assembling cake, mix half the package of coconut into the sour cream mixture.
Put sour cream mixture between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 days before serving.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter gradually.
Add sugar until you can work mixture with hands.
Place enough chocolate in candy paper cup to fill the bottom.
Then place a ball of mixture into center of the cup.
Fill the cup with chocolate.
Necessary chocolate can be purchased at a craft or candy shop.

title: buttery cinnamon skillet apples
directions: In heavy skillet, melt butter over medium heat (3 to 4 minutes).
Stir in sugar and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook spooning sauce over apples occasionally, until they are fork tender and sauce is thickened (12 to 15 minutes).

title: asparagus and pea casserole
directions: Saute green onions in butter.
Add garlic cheese and cook until melted.
Add mushroom soup, mushrooms, pimentos and water chestnuts (chopped).
Mix well and cook until mixtures bubbles in large casserole.
Pour drained asparagus and peas.
Spread cheese mixture evenly over top.
Bake 30 minutes or until sauce bubbles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple plus cake
directions: Cream butter and margarine.
Add sugar and blend well.
Beat in eggs.
Mix in vanilla and flour that has been sifted with salt and soda.
Add apples, nuts and coconut.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour at 300°, then 25 minutes

title: patty's freezer pickles
directions: Add cucumbers, salt and onion.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Let stand 1 hour and freeze. Freeze in 1/2 pints or whatever you want to freeze in.
(Small cucumbers make the best size to freeze.)

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Blend all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: simple apple sauce
directions: Peel apples and cut them into quarters (or smaller). In small pot combine apples, water, and sugar. Put heat on low and simmer mixture for about 1/2 hour. With a masher or fork, mash apples to form applesauce. Cinnamon can be added to taste.

title: lemon squares
directions: Pour over hot crust and then bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and then sprinkle powdered sugar over top.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in tube pan at 375° for 1 hour.

title: carrots in orange sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and simmer until barely tender.
Uncover and simmer until liquid evaporates.
Serves 6.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix sugar, baking soda, baking powder, oil, flour, buttermilk and yeast.
Beat with large spoon and put in a large sealed container.
Store in refrigerator and use as needed.
They do not have to rise.
Keeps well for several days.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: pecan icebox cookies
directions: Mix and roll into rolls. Place rolls into waxed paper. Put into the freezer. Slice and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until done.

title: drew's onion dill bread(automatic bread machine)
directions: Put yeast into inner pan of automatic bread machine.
Next, put flour, baking soda and salt in pan.
Break egg into flour mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients; warm and add to flour mixture.
Select white bread and push start.

title: pecan cheese balls
directions: In a small bowl, whip together cheese and sour cream.
Shape into small balls; roll in pecans.
Chill.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, sour cream, vanilla; then mix in dry ingredients.
Put in a greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle raisins or chocolate chips on top.
Then crumb topping.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Then drip with frosting.

title: old fashion jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; add eggs and beat.
In separate bowl, sift flour with spices and soda.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternating with the sour milk. Gradually add jam and nut meats.
Pour into 3 greased 9 inch cake pans.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt margarine and mix with crumbs.
Place in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Into a bowl, sift together the first 4 dry ingredients. Blend in the cold
butter until mixture resembles coarse meal. With a fork, stir in
1/2 cup milk and egg.
Add gradually 1/4 to 1/3 cup additional
milk if needed to bind the dough.
Turn onto lightly floured surface
and knead once or twice, patting dough into 3/4-inch thick
round.
With 2-inch cutter or glass bottom, cut out rounds
and
transfer
to
a
buttered
baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven
for
minutes
or
until golden. Makes about 16 biscuits.

title: steamed brown bread
directions: Sift white flour with soda and salt; add sugar and graham flour.
Add remaining ingredients; beat well.
Half-fill 4 greased 1-pound fruit cans; cover tightly and steam 1 1/2 hours on rack in covered pan, using small amount of boiling water.

title: beef skillet fiesta
directions: Brown meat in oil, add all other ingredients.
Bring to boil reduce heat to simmer and cook for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mother's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until al dente (about 4 to 5 minutes).
Thinly slice cheese to place on top; set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°. Cube remaining cheese.
Drain cooked macaroni; add tomato sauce, water, Worcestershire and dry mustard.
Stir in cheese.
Pour macaroni into a greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Lay cheese slices on top.
Cook in oven 20 to 30 minutes.
Check after 20 minutes.
It should be bubbling, but not too brown.
Let sit for a few minutes before serving.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir to blend. Spoon into Mason jar.
Tighten and keep refrigerated.

title: buttered brown potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut each one in six slices.
Dry with paper towel.
Coat in 1/4 cup butter in 2-quart baking dish.
Add salt, pepper and bacon bits.
Bake, covered, in single layer 20 minutes. Uncover.
Baste again and bake 30 minutes.

title: regina mayfield's baked spinach dip
directions: Saute onion in oil for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add Ro-Tel sauce and cook 2 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: italian green beans
directions: Cook green beans until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Add onion and dressing.
Simmer 5 minutes or until onion is tender.
Garnish with tomato.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, heat milk and soup to boiling.
Stir in raw broccoli, carrots and cauliflower.
Return to boiling.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. (Add extra milk, if needed, to keep from boiling dry.)
Stir in Cheddar cheese.
Heat through and serve.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Drain mushrooms, saving liquid.
Brown beef, mushrooms and onion.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add mushroom liquid, water, Heinz 57 and parsley; simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Pour over noodles.
Serves 6.

title: tart b.b.q. sauce
directions: Brown onion and celery in oil. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 mins. Makes 2 cups of sauce.

title: diabetic dessert - applesauce cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening until fluffy.
Beat egg and sugar substitute until lemon colored; add to shortening and blend well.
Sift together all dry ingredients; add to shortening mixture alternately with applesauce, blending well after each addition.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Stir in raisins.

title: tart 'n tangy tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use in sandwich or on lettuce.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 370° for 10 minutes until golden brown.
Cool.
Cream Miracle Whip, sour cream, cream cheese, dill weed and chives.
Spread on baked rolls.
Add desired vegetables (diced/sliced thin:
onions, broccoli, green pepper, tomatoes, cauliflower, zucchini, cukes, olives or radishes). Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over top.
Double recipe and place on cookie sheet.
Chill and cut in small squares.

title: genoese chicken and celery
directions: Use a little oil to brown washed and cut up chicken.
Add chopped garlic and continue to brown.
Remove from heat.
Wash and cut celery into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Add celery, shredded tomatoes, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and olives (liquid also).
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with boiled rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Combine potatoes, milk, sugar, butter, egg and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Top with marshmallows.
Broil until marshmallows are lightly browned.
(Be careful, marshmallows brown in seconds.)

title: orange slush
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed above.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
Great for breakfast or snacks.
Very pretty served in stemmed glassware!

title: chinese salad
directions: Mix coleslaw, chopped green onions, crushed Ramen noodles, seeds and almonds together. Add remaining ingredients and stir.
